019	PSA	004	006	Many say, “Who will show us happiness? Let shine brightly over us the light of thy countenance, O Lord.”
019	PSA	004	007	[But] thou hast placed more joy in my heart than at the time when their corn and their wine were increased.
019	PSA	004	008	In peace, altogether, will I lay me down and sleep; for thou, Lord, alone, causest me to dwell in safety.
019	PSA	005	001	“To the chief musician upon Nechiloth, a psalm of David.” To my words give ear, O Lord, have regard to my mediation.
019	PSA	005	002	Listen unto the voice of my loud cry, my King, and my God, when unto thee I pray.
019	PSA	005	003	O Lord! in the morning do thou hear my voice: in the morning will I set in order [my prayer] before thee, and 1ook up with hope.
019	PSA	005	004	For thou art not a God that hath pleasure in wickedness: evil cannot abide with thee.
019	PSA	005	005	The arrogant cannot stand up before thy eyes: thou hatest all workers of wickedness.
019	PSA	005	006	Thou wilt destroy those that speak lies: the man of blood and deceit the Lord abhorreth.
019	PSA	005	007	But as for me—in the abundance of thy kindness will I enter thy house: I will bow myself down before thy holy temple in the fear of thee.
019	PSA	005	008	O Lord, lead me in thy righteousness because of those that regard me enviously; make straight before me thy way.
019	PSA	005	009	For there is not in their mouth any sincerity; their inward part is full of deception; an open sepulchre is their throat: they flatter with their tongue.
019	PSA	005	010	Condemn them, O God: let them fall through their own counsels; for the multitude of their transgressions cast them down; for they have rebelled against thee.
019	PSA	005	011	Then will rejoice all those that put their trust in thee; for ever will they shout for joy, when thou protectest them: and then will exult in thee those that love thy name.
019	PSA	005	012	For thou wilt bless the righteous, O Lord; as with a shield wilt thou encompass him with favor.
019	PSA	006	001	“To the chief musician on Neginoth upon Sheminith, a psalm of David.” O Lord, correct me not in thy anger, and chastise me not in thy wrath.
019	PSA	006	002	Be gracious unto me, O Lord; for I am withering away; heal me, O Lord; for my bones are terrified.
019	PSA	006	003	And my soul is greatly terrified; but thou, O Lord, how long yet—?
019	PSA	006	004	Return, O Lord, deliver my soul: help me for the sake of thy kindness.
019	PSA	006	005	For in death men do not remember thee: in the nether world, who shall give thee thanks?
019	PSA	006	006	I am weary with my sighing; I flood every night my bed; With my tears I moisten my couch.
019	PSA	006	007	My eye is consumed because of grief; it waxeth old because of all my assailants.
019	PSA	006	008	Depart from me, all ye workers of wickedness; for the Lord hath heard the voice of my weeping.
019	PSA	006	009	The Lord hath heard my supplication; the Lord will accept my prayer.
019	PSA	006	010	Ashamed and greatly terrified shall become all my enemies; they will turn round, and be made ashamed in a moment.
019	PSA	007	001	“A Shiggayon of David, which he sang unto the Lord, concerning the affairs of Cush the Benjamite.” O Lord my God, in thee do I put my trust; save me from every one of my persecutors, and deliver me:
019	PSA	007	002	Lest he tear like a lion my soul, rending it in pieces, with none to deliver.
019	PSA	007	003	O Lord my God, if I have done this; if there be injustice in my hands;
019	PSA	007	004	If I have recompensed him that was at peace with me with evil; If I have taken aught from my assailants without cause:
019	PSA	007	005	May the enemy hotly pursue my soul, and overtake it; and tread down upon the earth my life, and cause my honor to be in the dust. (Selah)
019	PSA	007	006	Arise, O Lord, in thy anger, lift up thyself because of the rage of my enemies: and awake for me [to] the judgment that thou hast commanded.
019	PSA	007	007	So shall the congregation of nations compass thee about: and for their sakes return thou to the height.
019	PSA	007	008	The Lord will judge the people: judge me, O Lord, according to my righteousness, and according to my integrity [grant] me [recompense].
019	PSA	007	009	Oh let the evil of the wicked come to an end; but establish the just, O thou, who triest the hearts and reins, O righteous God.
019	PSA	007	010	My protection is by God, who saveth the upright in heath.
019	PSA	007	011	God is a righteous judge, and a God who is indignant [with the wicked] every day.
019	PSA	007	012	If he turn not, He will whet his sword, he bendeth his bow, and maketh it ready.
019	PSA	007	013	Also for him he prepareth the instruments of death; he fashioneth his arrows against the persecutors.
019	PSA	007	014	Behold, he travaileth with wrong doing; but he hath conceived mischief, and bringeth forth falsehood.
019	PSA	007	015	He hath hollowed out a pit, and dug it, and is fallen into the ditch which he hath wrought.
019	PSA	007	016	His mischief will return upon his own head, and upon his own skull will his violence come down.
019	PSA	007	017	I will thank the Lord according to his righteousness; and I will sing praises to the name of the Lord the Most High.
019	PSA	008	001	“To the chief musician upon Gittith, a psalm of David.” O Eternal One our Lord, how excellent is thy name on all the earth! thou who hast set thy majesty above the heavens.
019	PSA	008	002	Out of the mouth of babes and sucklings hast thou founded [thy] might, because of thy opponents, that thou mightest bring to silence the enemy and him that seeketh vengeance.
019	PSA	008	003	When I behold thy heavens, the work of thy fingers, the moon and the stars, which thou hast established: —
019	PSA	008	004	What is the mortal, that thou rememberest him? and the son of man, that thou thinkest of him:
019	PSA	008	005	Yet thou hast made him but a little less than angels, and hast crowned him with honor and glory.
019	PSA	008	006	Thou hast given him dominion over the works of thy hands; every thing hast thou placed beneath his feet:
019	PSA	008	007	Flocks and herds altogether, and also the beasts of the field;
019	PSA	008	008	The birds of heaven, and the fishes of the sea, whatsoever passeth through the paths of the seas.
019	PSA	008	009	O Eternal One our Lord, how excellent is thy name on all the earth!
019	PSA	009	001	“To the chief musician upon Muthlabben, a psalm of David.” I will thank the Lord with all my heart: I will relate all thy marvelous deeds.
019	PSA	009	002	I will rejoice and exult in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou Most High:
019	PSA	009	003	When my enemies are turned backward, [when] they fall and perish at thy presence.
019	PSA	009	004	For thou hast conducted my dispute and my cause; thou hast sat on the throne as a righteous judge.
019	PSA	009	005	Thou hast rebuked nations, thou hast caused the wicked to perish, their name hast thou blotted out for ever and ever.
019	PSA	009	006	O thou enemy, the ruins are passed away for ever, and the cities which thou hast destroyed, —lost is their memorial, yea, theirs.
019	PSA	009	007	But the Lord will sit enthroned for ever: he hath established for giving judgment his throne.
019	PSA	009	008	And he will judge the world with righteousness, he shall decide for the people, with equity.
019	PSA	009	009	The Lord also will be a strong-hold for the oppressed, a strong-hold in times of distress.
019	PSA	009	010	And they that know thy name will put their trust in thee; for thou hast not forsaken those that seek thee, O Lord.
019	PSA	009	011	Sing praises to the Lord, who dwelleth in Zion: announce among the people his deeds.
019	PSA	009	012	For he, that inquireth after acts of blood, hath remembered them: he hath not forgotten the cry of the afflicted.
019	PSA	009	013	Be gracious unto me, O Lord; have regard to my affliction [coming] from those that hate me, thou who liftest me up from the gates of death:
019	PSA	009	014	In order that I may relate all thy praises in the gates of the daughters of Zion: I will be glad in thy salvation.
019	PSA	009	015	Sunk are nations in the ditch that they have prepared: in this net which they had laid in secret is their own foot caught.
019	PSA	009	016	The Lord is made known: he executed justice: through the doing of his own hands is the wicked ensnared. Higgayon, (Selah)
019	PSA	009	017	The wicked shall return into hell, all the nations that are forgetful of God.
019	PSA	009	018	For not everlastingly shall the needy be forgotten: the expectation of the poor shall not perish for ever.
019	PSA	009	019	Arise, O Lord; let not the mortal boast of his strength; let nations be judged before thy face.
019	PSA	009	020	Place, O Lord, fear over them: let nations know, that they are but mortals. (Selah)
019	PSA	010	001	Wherefore, O Lord, standest thou afar off? hidest thyself in times of distress?
019	PSA	010	002	In the pride of the wicked doth he hotly pursue the poor: they are seized through the plans that those have devised.
019	PSA	010	003	For the wicked boasteth of the longing of his soul, and the robber blesseth himself when he hath despised the Lord.
019	PSA	010	004	The wicked, according to the pride of his wrathfulness, [saith,] He will not require, There is no God [in] all his plans.
019	PSA	010	005	Prosperous are his ways at all times; far in the height [remain] thy punishments away from him: all his assailants—he puffeth at them.
019	PSA	010	006	He saith in his heart, I shall not be moved; I shall be for many generations, and without adversity.
019	PSA	010	007	Of the false oaths is his mouth full, and deceit and fraud: under his tongue is mischief and wickedness.
019	PSA	010	008	He sitteth in the lurking-places of the villages; in the secret places doth he murder the innocent: his eyes search for the unfortunate.
019	PSA	010	009	He lieth in wait in a secret place like a lion in his den; he lieth in wait to snatch up the poor: he snatcheth up the poor, as they draweth him into his net.
019	PSA	010	010	He croucheth, he bendeth himself, and the unfortunate fall through his might.
019	PSA	010	011	He saith in his heart, God hath forgotten; he hath hidden his face; he will never see it.
019	PSA	010	012	Arise, O Lord; O God, lift up thy hand: forget not the afflicted.
019	PSA	010	013	For what doth the wicked despise God? [why] doth he say in his heart, Thou wilt not require it?
019	PSA	010	014	Thou hast seen it: for thou beholdest mischief and despiteful acts, to requite it with thy hand: unto thee the unfortunate committeth himself; unto the fatherless hast thou [ever] been a helper.
019	PSA	010	015	Break thou the arm of the wicked; and of the bad man—thou wilt inquire for his wickedness [till] thou find none.
019	PSA	010	016	The Lord is King for ever and ever: nations are perished out of his land.
019	PSA	010	017	The longing of the afflicted dost thou hear, O Lord! thou wilt strengthen their heart, thou wilt cause thy ear to listen:
019	PSA	010	018	To judge the fatherless and the oppressed, that not farther more shall be arrogant the mortal from the earth.
019	PSA	011	001	“To the chief musician, by David.” In the Lord have I put my trust: how can ye say to my soul, Flee to your mountain as a bird?
019	PSA	011	002	For lo, the wicked bend their bow, they arrange their arrow upon the string, to shoot in the dark at the upright in heart.
019	PSA	011	003	For [if] the foundations be torn down, what can the righteous do?
019	PSA	011	004	The Lord is in his holy temple, the Lord hath his throne in the heavens, his eyes behold, his eyelids prove, the children of men.
019	PSA	011	005	The Lord proveth the righteous; but the wicked and him that loveth violence his soul hateth.
019	PSA	011	006	He letteth rain upon the wicked burning coals, fire and brimstone; and a glowing wind is the portion of their cup.
019	PSA	011	007	For righteous is the Lord, he loveth righteousness: his countenance doth behold the upright.
019	PSA	012	001	“To the chief musician upon Sheminith, a psalm of David.” Help, O Lord; for the pious have ceased to be; for the truthful have failed from among the children of men.
019	PSA	012	002	Deceptively do they speak every one with his neighbor, with flattering lips, with a double heart do they speak.
019	PSA	012	003	May the Lord cut off all flattering lips, the tongue that speaketh boastful things:
019	PSA	012	004	Who have said, With our tongue will we be mighty; our lips are with us; who is Lord over us!
019	PSA	012	005	Because of the oppression of the poor, because of the sighing of the needy, now will I arise, saith the Lord: I will grant safety to him for whom the other layeth a snare.
019	PSA	012	006	The words of the Lord are pure words, as silver refined in the crucible of earth, purified seven times.
019	PSA	012	007	Thou, O Lord, wilt preserve them; thou wilt guard them from this generation for ever.
019	PSA	012	008	On every side do the wicked walk about, when the vile are exalted over the sons of man.
019	PSA	013	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David.” How long, O Lord, wilt thou forget me continually! how long wilt thou hide thy face from me?
019	PSA	013	002	How long shall I have to devise resolves in my soul, with grief in my heart daily? how long shall my enemy exalt himself over me?
019	PSA	013	003	Look down, answer me, O Lord my God! enlighten my eyes, that I may not sleep the sleep of death;
019	PSA	013	004	That my enemy may not say, I have overcome him; that my assailants may not be glad when I am moved.
019	PSA	013	005	But I trust in thy kindness, let my heart be glad because of thy salvation:
019	PSA	013	006	I will sing unto the Lord, because he hath dealt bountifully with me.
019	PSA	014	001	“To the chief musician, by David.” The worthless fool saith in his heart, There is no God. They are corrupt, they are abominable [in their] doings, there is none that doth good.
019	PSA	014	002	The Lord looketh down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there be one intelligent, one who seeketh for God.
019	PSA	014	003	They are all gone aside, they are altogether become corrupt: there is none that doth good, no, not even one.
019	PSA	014	004	Is there no knowledge in all the workers of wickedness? who eat up my people as they eat bread; [while] they do not call on the Lord.
019	PSA	014	005	There are they terrified in terror; for God is with the righteous generation:
019	PSA	014	006	The counsel of the poor [though] you put to shame; because the Lord is his protection.
019	PSA	014	007	Oh that some one might bring the salvation of Israel out of Zion! When the Lord bringeth back the captivity of his people, then will Jacob be glad, and Israel will rejoice.
019	PSA	015	001	“A psalm of David.” Lord, who may sojourn in thy tent? who may dwell on thy holy mount?
019	PSA	015	002	He that walketh uprightly, and worketh righteousness, and speaketh the truth in his heart;
019	PSA	015	003	That uttereth no calumny with his tongue, that doth no evil to his neighbor, and bringeth no reproach on his fellow-man;
019	PSA	015	004	In whose eyes the despicable is despised; but that honoreth those who fear the Lord; that sweareth to his own injury, and changeth not;
019	PSA	015	005	That putteth not out his money for interest, and taketh no bribe against the innocent. He that doth these things shall not be moved to eternity.
019	PSA	016	001	“A Michtham of David.” Preserve me, O God; for I have placed my trust in thee.
019	PSA	016	002	[O my soul], thou hast said unto the Lord, Thou art my Lord: my happiness is not without thee;
019	PSA	016	003	[But] in the saints who are on the earth, and in the excellent—in them is all my delight.
019	PSA	016	004	Multiplied shall be the sorrows of those who give presents to another god: I will not pour out their drink-offerings of blood, nor bear their names upon my lips.
019	PSA	016	005	Thou, O Lord, art the portion of my inheritance, and my cup; thou hast drawn my lot.
019	PSA	016	006	My possessions are fallen in agreeable places: yea, my heritage is pleasant to me.
019	PSA	016	007	I will bless the Lord, who hath given me counsel: also in the night seasons my reins admonish me.
019	PSA	016	008	I have always set the Lord before me, that, being at my right hand, I might not be moved.
019	PSA	016	009	Therefore is rejoiced my heart, and my spirit is glad: also my flesh shall rest in safety.
019	PSA	016	010	For thou wilt not abandon my soul to the grave: thou wilt not suffer thy pious [servant] to see corruption.
019	PSA	016	011	Thou wilt let me know the path of life: fulness of joy is in thy presence; pleasures are at thy right hand for evermore.
019	PSA	017	001	“A prayer of David.” Hear, O Lord, [the cause of] righteousness, attend unto my entreaty, give ear unto my prayer, coming from lips without deceit.
019	PSA	017	002	Let from thy presence my sentence come forth; let thy eyes behold what is right.
019	PSA	017	003	Thou hast proved my heart; thou hast thought of me in the night; thou hast refined me—thou couldst find nothing: my purpose doth not pass beyond [the words of] my mouth.
019	PSA	017	004	Among the deeds of men did I observe, by the word of thy lips, the paths of the dissolute.
019	PSA	017	005	My steps held firmly to thy tracks, [and] my footsteps did not slip.
019	PSA	017	006	I call on thee, for thou wilt answer me, O God: incline thy ear unto me, hear my speech.
019	PSA	017	007	Show marvelously thy loving-kindnesses, O thou that savest those who put their trust [in thee] from those that rise up [against them] by thy right hand.
019	PSA	017	008	Keep me as the apple of the eye; conceal me under the shadow of thy wings,
019	PSA	017	009	From the wicked that despoil me, my enemies, who, to take my life, compass me about.
019	PSA	017	010	They are enclosed in their own fat: with their mouth they speak proudly.
019	PSA	017	011	On our steps they now encompass us: they direct their eyes to turn aside in the land.
019	PSA	017	012	Every man is just like a lion that is greedy to tear his prey, and like a young lion lurking in a covert.
019	PSA	017	013	Arise, O Lord, prevent him, cast him down; deliver my soul from the wicked, who is thy sword, —
019	PSA	017	014	From these men—thy hand—O Lord, from the men of this world, whose portion is in this life, and whose belly thou fillest with thy hidden treasure: they have children in plenty, and leave the rest of their substance to their babes.
019	PSA	017	015	As for me, in righteousness shall I behold thy face: I shall be satisfied, when I awake, with contemplating thy likeness.
019	PSA	018	001	“To the chief musician, by the servant of the Lord, by David, who spoke unto the Lord the words of this song on the day that the Lord had delivered him out of the power of all his enemies, and from the hand of Saul; And he said,” I ever love thee, O Lord, my strength.
019	PSA	018	002	The Lord is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer; my God, my rock, in whom I trust; my shield, and the horn of my salvation, and my high tower.
019	PSA	018	003	Praised, I cried, be the Lord, and from my enemies was I saved.
019	PSA	018	004	The bonds of death encompassed me, and the floods of destruction made me afraid.
019	PSA	018	005	The bonds of hell encircled me: the snares of death seized on me.
019	PSA	018	006	[When] in my distress I called upon the Lord, and unto my God I cried: he heard from his temple my voice, and my complaint came before him, even into his ears.
019	PSA	018	007	Then shook and trembled the earth; and the foundations of the mountains were moved; and they were shaken, because he was wroth.
019	PSA	018	008	Smoke went up in his anger and consuming fire out of his mouth: coals flamed forth from him.
019	PSA	018	009	And he bent the heavens, and came down: and thick darkness was under his feet:
019	PSA	018	010	And he rode upon a cherub, and flew along, and he flitted by upon the wings of the wind.
019	PSA	018	011	He made darkness his hiding-place, round about him as his pavilion, dark waters, thick clouds of the skies.
019	PSA	018	012	From the brightness before him his thick clouds passed away, [with] hail-stones and coals of fire.
019	PSA	018	013	And the Lord thundered in the heavens, and the Most High uttered forth his voice, [with] hail-stones and coals of fire.
019	PSA	018	014	And he sent out his arrows, and scattered them; and he shot forth lightnings, and discomfited them.
019	PSA	018	015	And then were seen the channels of the waters, and there were laid open the foundations of the world, through thy rebuke, O Lord, through the blast of the breath of thy nostrils.
019	PSA	018	016	He stretched out from above [his hand], he took me; he drew me out from mighty waters.
019	PSA	018	017	He delivered me from my enemy, the strong, and from those that hated me, when they were too mighty for me.
019	PSA	018	018	They overcame me on the day of my calamity; but the Lord became my stay.
019	PSA	018	019	And he brought me forth into a large space; he delivered me, because he had delight in me.
019	PSA	018	020	The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the purity of my hands did he recompense me.
019	PSA	018	021	For I have kept the ways of the Lord, and have not wickedly departed from my God.
019	PSA	018	022	For all his ordinances were before me, and his statutes had I not put away from me.
019	PSA	018	023	I was also upright with him, and I guarded myself against my iniquity.
019	PSA	018	024	Therefore did the Lord recompense me according to my righteousness, according to the purity of my hands before his eyes.
019	PSA	018	025	With the kind thou wilt show thyself kind; with the upright man thou wilt show thyself upright;
019	PSA	018	026	With the pure thou wilt show thyself pure; and with the perverse thou wilt wage a contest.
019	PSA	018	027	For thou wilt indeed save the afflicted people; but haughty eyes wilt thou bring down.
019	PSA	018	028	For thou wilt cause my light to shine: the Lord my God will enlighten my darkness.
019	PSA	018	029	For [aided] by thee I run through a troop; and [helped] by my God I leap over a wall.
019	PSA	018	030	As for God, —his way is perfect; the word of the Lord is tried: he is a shield to all those that trust in him.
019	PSA	018	031	For who is God save the Lord? or who is a rock beside our God?
019	PSA	018	032	He is the God that girdeth me with strength, and rendereth my way unobstructed.
019	PSA	018	033	He maketh my feet like those of the hinds, and upon my high-places he causeth me to stand.
019	PSA	018	034	He teacheth my hands for the war, so that a brazen bow is bent by my arms.
019	PSA	018	035	And thou gavest me the shield of thy salvation, and thy right hand supported me: and thy meekness hath made me great.
019	PSA	018	036	Thou enlargest my steps under me, so that my joints do not slip.
019	PSA	018	037	I pursue my enemies, and overtake them; and I return not again till I have made an end of them.
019	PSA	018	038	I crush them that they are not able to rise: they fall under my feet.
019	PSA	018	039	For thou hast girded me with strength for the war: thou subduest my opponents under me.
019	PSA	018	040	And my enemies thou causest to turn their back to me; and those that hate me, —that I may destroy them.
019	PSA	018	041	They cry, but there is none to help; unto the Lord, —but he answereth them not.
019	PSA	018	042	And I beat them small as the dust before the wind: like the dirt in the streets do I cast them out.
019	PSA	018	043	Thou deliverest me from the contests of the people; thou appointest me to be the head of nations: a people that I know not shall serve me.
019	PSA	018	044	As soon as their ear heareth they shall be obedient to me: the children of the stranger shall utter flattery unto me.
019	PSA	018	045	The children of the stranger shall fade away, and come forth trembling out of their close places.
019	PSA	018	046	The Lord liveth, and blessed be my Rock; and exalted be the God of my salvation;
019	PSA	018	047	The God that granteth me vengeance, and subdueth nations under me;
019	PSA	018	048	That delivereth me from my enemies: also above my opponents thou liftest me up; thou deliverest me from the man of violence.
019	PSA	018	049	Therefore will I give thanks unto thee among the nations, O Lord, and unto thy name will I sing praises, —
019	PSA	018	050	[To him] that maketh great the salvation of his king, and who sheweth kindness to his anointed, to David, and to his seed for ever.
019	PSA	019	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David.” The heavens relate the glory of God; and the expanse telleth of the works of his hands.
019	PSA	019	002	Day unto day uttereth speech, and night unto night showeth knowledge.
019	PSA	019	003	There is no speech, there are no words, their voice is not heard.
019	PSA	019	004	[But] their melody extendeth through all the earth, and to the end of the world their words. For the sun hath he set a tabernacle among them;
019	PSA	019	005	And he goeth out as a bridegroom from his chamber, he is glad like a strong man to run his course;
019	PSA	019	006	From the end of the heavens is his going forth, and his circuit is unto their ends: and there is nothing hidden from his heat.
019	PSA	019	007	The law of the Lord is perfect, quieting the soul: the testimony of the Lord is sure, making wise the simple.
019	PSA	019	008	The precepts of the Lord are upright, rejoicing the heart; the commandment of the Lord is clear, enlightening the eyes.
019	PSA	019	009	The fear of the Lord is pure, enduring for ever: the ordinances of the Lord are the truth, they are just altogether.
019	PSA	019	010	They are those which are to be desired more than gold, and much fine gold; and they are sweeter than honey and the dropping of honeycomb.
019	PSA	019	011	Moreover thy servant is admonished by them: in keeping them there is great reward.
019	PSA	019	012	Who can guard against errors? from secret [faults] do thou cleanse me.
019	PSA	019	013	Also from presumptuous [sins] withhold thy servant; let them not have dominion over me: then shall I be blameless, and I shall be clear from any great transgression.
019	PSA	019	014	May the words of my mouth, and the meditation of my heart, be acceptable before thee, O Lord, my Rock, and my Redeemer.
019	PSA	020	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David.” May the Lord answer thee on the day of distress; may the name of the God of Jacob protect thee;
019	PSA	020	002	May he send thee help from the sanctuary, and support thee from Zion;
019	PSA	020	003	May he remember all thy meat-offerings, and accept in favor thy burnt-sacrifice. (Selah)
019	PSA	020	004	May he grant thee according to thy own heart, and fulfill all thy resolves.
019	PSA	020	005	We will rejoice in thy salvation, and in the name of our God will we upraise our banners: may the Lord fulfill all thy petitions.
019	PSA	020	006	Now I know that the Lord saveth his anointed: he will answer him from his holy heavens, with the saving strength of his right hand.
019	PSA	020	007	Some [trust] in chariots, and some in horses; but we will invoke the name of the Lord our God.
019	PSA	020	008	They are prostrate and fallen; but we are risen up and stand erect.
019	PSA	020	009	O Lord, save [us]: may the king answer us on the day when we call [on him].
019	PSA	021	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David.” O Lord, because of thy strength will the king rejoice; and through thy salvation how greatly will he be glad!
019	PSA	021	002	The longing of his heart hast thou given him, and the request of his lips hast thou not withholden. (Selah)
019	PSA	021	003	For thou meetest him unasked with the blessings of happiness: thou settest on his head a crown of pure gold.
019	PSA	021	004	Life hath he asked of thee, thou gavest it to him, length of days for ever and ever.
019	PSA	021	005	Great is his honor through thy help: glory and majesty thou layest upon him.
019	PSA	021	006	For thou appointest him to be a blessing for ever: thou makest him glad with joy from thy presence.
019	PSA	021	007	For the king trusteth in the Lord; and through the kindness of the Most High shall he not be moved.
019	PSA	021	008	Thy hand will reach all thy enemies: thy right hand will reach those that hate thee.
019	PSA	021	009	Thou wilt render them as a fiery oven at the time of thy anger: the Lord in his wrath will destroy them, and a fire will devour them.
019	PSA	021	010	Their fruit wilt thou cause to perish from the earth, and their seed from among the children of men.
019	PSA	021	011	For they directed against thee evil: they devised a mischievous purpose, which they were not able to perform.
019	PSA	021	012	For thou wilt make them turn their back; upon thy bow-strings thou wilt make ready [thy arrows] against their face.
019	PSA	021	013	Exalt thyself, O Lord, in thy strength; [and] we will sing and praise thy power.
019	PSA	022	001	“To the chief musician upon Ayeleth-hashachar, a psalm of David.” My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me? why art thou so far from saving me, and from the words of my loud complaint?
019	PSA	022	002	O my God! I call in the day-time, but thou answerest not; and in the night I find no rest.
019	PSA	022	003	But thou art holy, O thou that dwellest amidst the praises of Israel.
019	PSA	022	004	In thee did our fathers trust: they trusted, and thou didst deliver them.
019	PSA	022	005	Unto thee they cried, and were delivered: in thee they trusted, and were not put to shame.
019	PSA	022	006	But I am a worm, and not a man, a reproach of men, and despised of people.
019	PSA	022	007	All those who see me laugh me to scorn: they draw open their lips, they shake their head, [saying,]
019	PSA	022	008	“Let him throw himself on the Lord, that he may deliver him: he will save him, for he delighteth in him.”
019	PSA	022	009	Yea, thou art he that took me from the womb: thou hast been my trust when I hung on my mother's breasts.
019	PSA	022	010	Upon thee was I cast from my birth: from my mother's womb art thou my God.
019	PSA	022	011	Oh be not far from me [now]; for distress is near; for there is none to help.
019	PSA	022	012	Many steers have encompassed me: the strong bulls of Bashan have beset me round.
019	PSA	022	013	They have opened wide against me their mouth, [as] a ravenous and roaring lion.
019	PSA	022	014	Like water am I poured out, and all my bones are disjointed: my heart is become like wax, it is melted in the midst of my entrails.
019	PSA	022	015	Like a potsherd is my strength dried up; and my tongue cleaveth to my palate; and into the dust of death hast thou laid me down.
019	PSA	022	016	For dogs have encompassed me; the assembly of the wicked have enclosed me: like lions [they threaten] my hands and my feet.
019	PSA	022	017	I may number all my bones: [while] they stare and look upon me.
019	PSA	022	018	They divide my clothes among themselves, and for my garment do they cast lots.
019	PSA	022	019	But thou, O Lord, be not far from me: O [thou who art] my strength, hasten to my aid.
019	PSA	022	020	Deliver from the sword my life, from the power of the dog my solitary soul.
019	PSA	022	021	Save me from the lion's mouth; as thou hast answered me from the horns of the reem.
019	PSA	022	022	I will relate thy name unto my brethren: in the midst of the congregation will I praise thee.
019	PSA	022	023	Ye that fear the Lord, praise him; all ye the seed of Jacob, glorify him; and be in dread of him, all ye the seed of Israel.
019	PSA	022	024	For he hath not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the poor; neither hath he hidden his face from him; but when he cried unto him, he heard.
019	PSA	022	025	Of thee shall be my praise in a great assembly: my vows will I pay in the presence of those who fear him.
019	PSA	022	026	The meek shall eat and be satisfied; they who seek him shall praise the Lord: may your heart live for ever.
019	PSA	022	027	All the ends of the world shall remember and return unto the Lord: and all the families of the nations shall bow themselves down before thee.
019	PSA	022	028	For the kingdom is the Lord's, and he governeth the nations.
019	PSA	022	029	All they that eat the fat of the earth shall bow themselves down; before him shall bend the knee all that are going down into the dust; for none can keep alive his own soul.
019	PSA	022	030	Distant ages shall serve him; there shall be related of the Lord unto future generations.
019	PSA	022	031	They will come, and will tell his righteousness unto a people yet unborn, that he hath done this.
019	PSA	023	001	“A psalm of David.” The Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.
019	PSA	023	002	In pastures of tender grass he causeth me to lie down: beside still waters he leadeth me.
019	PSA	023	003	My soul he refresheth: he guideth me in the tracks of righteousness for the sake of his name.
019	PSA	023	004	Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will not fear evil; for thou art with me: thy rod and thy staff—they indeed comfort me.
019	PSA	023	005	Thou preparest before me a table in the presence of my assailants; thou anointest with oil my head: my cup overfloweth.
019	PSA	023	006	Surely, only goodness and kindness shall follow me all the days of my life: and I shall dwell in the house of the Lord to the utmost length of days.
019	PSA	024	001	“Of David a psalm.” Unto the Lord belongeth the earth with what filleth it, the world and they that dwell therein;
019	PSA	024	002	For upon seas hath he founded it, and upon rivers hath he established it.
019	PSA	024	003	Who shall ascend into the mountain of the Lord? and who shall be able to stand in his holy place?
019	PSA	024	004	He that is of clean hands, and pure of heart; who hath not lifted up his soul unto falsehood, and hath not sworn deceitfully:
019	PSA	024	005	He shall bear away blessing from the Lord, and [the reward of] righteousness from the God of his salvation.
019	PSA	024	006	This is the generation of those that adore him, that seek thy presence, [the sons of] Jacob. (Selah)
019	PSA	024	007	Raise your heads, O ye gates; and be raised wide, ye everlasting doors: and let the King of glory enter!
019	PSA	024	008	Who is this King of glory? The Lord strong and mighty, the Lord mighty in battle.
019	PSA	024	009	Raise your heads, O ye gates; and raise [them] up, ye everlasting doors: and let the King of glory enter!
019	PSA	024	010	Who is then this King of glory? The Lord of hosts, he is the King of glory. (Selah)
019	PSA	025	001	“Of David.” Unto thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.
019	PSA	025	002	O my God, in thee do I trust, let me not be ashamed, let not my enemies triumph over me.
019	PSA	025	003	Yea, none that wait on thee will be put to shame: let those be put to shame who deal treacherously without cause.
019	PSA	025	004	Show me, O Lord, thy ways; teach me thy paths.
019	PSA	025	005	Lead me in thy truth, and teach me; for thou art the God of my salvation: on thee do I wait all the day.
019	PSA	025	006	Remember thy mercies, O Lord, and thy kindnesses; for they are from everlasting.
019	PSA	025	007	The sins of my youth and my transgressions do not remember: according to thy kindness bear thou me in remembrance, for the sake of thy goodness, O Lord.
019	PSA	025	008	Good and upright is the Lord: therefore he pointeth out to sinners the right way.
019	PSA	025	009	He guideth the meek in justice, and he teacheth the meek his way.
019	PSA	025	010	All the paths of the Lord are kindness and truth unto such as keep his covenant and his testimonies.
019	PSA	025	011	For the sake of thy name, O Lord, pardon my iniquity: although it is great.
019	PSA	025	012	Who is that man that feareth the Lord? to him will he point out the way which he is to choose?
019	PSA	025	013	His soul shall abide in happiness: and his seed shall inherit the land.
019	PSA	025	014	The secret counsel of the Lord is for those that fear him, and his covenant—to make it known to them.
019	PSA	025	015	My eyes are ever [directed] toward the Lord; for he will draw out of the net my feet.
019	PSA	025	016	Turn unto me, and be gracious unto me; for I am solitary and afflicted.
019	PSA	025	017	The distresses of my heart are enlarged: O bring thou me out of my afflictions.
019	PSA	025	018	Look on my misery and my trouble; and forgive all my sins.
019	PSA	025	019	Look at my enemies; for they are many; and they hate me with the hatred of violence.
019	PSA	025	020	Oh, guard my soul; and deliver me: let me not be put to shame; for I put my trust in thee.
019	PSA	025	021	Let integrity and uprightness guard me; for I wait on thee.
019	PSA	025	022	Redeem, O God, Israel out of all his distresses.
019	PSA	026	001	“Of David.” Judge me, O Lord; for I have indeed walked in my integrity: and in the Lord have I trusted; I shall not slip.
019	PSA	026	002	Try me, O Lord, and prove me; purify my reins and my heart.
019	PSA	026	003	For thy kindness is before my eyes; and I have walked in thy truth.
019	PSA	026	004	I have not sat with men of falsehood, and with dissemblers will I not enter [in communion].
019	PSA	026	005	I have hated the assemblage of evil-doers; and with the wicked will I not sit.
019	PSA	026	006	I will wash in innocency my hands, and I will compass thy altar, O Lord:
019	PSA	026	007	That I may publish with a loud voice [my] thanksgiving, and relate all thy wondrous deeds.
019	PSA	026	008	Lord, I love the site of thy house, and the place where thy glory dwelleth.
019	PSA	026	009	Take not away with sinners my soul, nor with men of blood my life;
019	PSA	026	010	In whose hands are wicked devices, and whose right hand is full of bribes.
019	PSA	026	011	But as for me, I will walk in my integrity: redeem me, and be gracious unto me.
019	PSA	026	012	My foot standeth on an even place: in assemblies will I bless the Lord.
019	PSA	027	001	“Of David.” The Lord is my light and my salvation; of whom shall I be afraid? the Lord is the fortress of my life; of whom shall I have dread?
019	PSA	027	002	When evil-doers come near against me to eat up my flesh, my assailants and my enemies at me: then do they stumble and fall.
019	PSA	027	003	If an army should encamp against me, my heart shall not fear: if war should arise against me, even then will I have trust.
019	PSA	027	004	One thing have I asked of the Lord, that I will seek for: that I may dwell in the house of the Lord all the days of my life, to behold the loveliness of the Lord, and to be every morning early in his temple.
019	PSA	027	005	For he will hide me in his pavilion on the day of evil; he will conceal me in the secret of his tabernacle; upon a rock will he place me high.
019	PSA	027	006	And now will my head be lifted up above my enemies all round about me; and I will sacrifice in his tabernacle sacrifices of joy: I will sing, and I will triumphantly play unto the Lord.
019	PSA	027	007	Hear, O Lord, my voice, [when] I call, and be gracious unto me, and answer me.
019	PSA	027	008	Of thee, said my heart, “Seek ye my presence”: thy presence, Lord, will I seek.
019	PSA	027	009	Hide [then] not thy face from me; reject not in anger thy servant, thou [who] hast been my help: cast me not off, nor forsake me, O God of my salvation.
019	PSA	027	010	For my father and my mother have forsaken me; but the Lord will take me up.
019	PSA	027	011	Point me out thy way, O Lord! and guide me on a level path, because of those that regard me enviously.
019	PSA	027	012	Give me not up to the [revengeful] desire of my assailants; for there are risen up against me false witnesses, and such as utter violence.
019	PSA	027	013	Unless I had believed to see the goodness of the Lord in the land of life—
019	PSA	027	014	Wait on the Lord; be strong, and let thy heart be of good courage; and only wait on the Lord.
019	PSA	028	001	“Of David.” Unto thee, O Lord, will I call; O my rock, turn not unheeding from me: lest thou turn away silent from me, and I become like those that go down into the pit.
019	PSA	028	002	Hear the voice of my supplications, when I cry unto thee, when I lift up my hands toward the most holy place of thy sanctuary.
019	PSA	028	003	Snatch me not away with the wicked, and with the workers of injustice, who speak peace with their neighbors, with mischief in their heart.
019	PSA	028	004	Give unto them according to their doing, and according to the evil of their deeds; according to the work of their hands do thou give unto them: bestow their [just] recompense on them.
019	PSA	028	005	Because they have no regard for the doings of the Lord, nor the works of his hands: may he pull them down, and not build them up.
019	PSA	028	006	Blessed be the Lord, because he hath heard the voice of my supplications.
019	PSA	028	007	The Lord is my strength and my shield; in him hath my heart trusted, and I am helped, and my heart exulteth; and with my song will I thank him.
019	PSA	028	008	The Lord is strength unto them, and he is the fortress of victory of his anointed.
019	PSA	028	009	Help thy people, and bless thy heritage: and feed them, and exalt them unto all eternity.
019	PSA	029	001	“A psalm of David.” Ascribe unto the Lord, O ye sons of the mighty, ascribe unto the Lord glory and strength.
019	PSA	029	002	Ascribe unto the Lord the glory of his name; bow down to the Lord in the beauty of holiness.
019	PSA	029	003	The voice of the Lord is upon the waters; the God of glory thundereth, the Lord—upon mighty waters.
019	PSA	029	004	The voice of the Lord [resoundeth] with power; the voice of the Lord [resoundeth] with majesty.
019	PSA	029	005	The voice of the Lord breaketh in pieces the cedars; yea, the Lord shivereth the cedars of Lebanon;
019	PSA	029	006	And he maketh them skip like a calf; Lebanon and Siryon like young reems.
019	PSA	029	007	The voice of the Lord heweth out flames of fire.
019	PSA	029	008	The voice of the Lord shaketh the wilderness; the Lord shaketh the wilderness of Kadesh.
019	PSA	029	009	The voice of the Lord causeth the hinds to start, and maketh bare forests: and in his temple every thing speaketh [of his] glory.
019	PSA	029	010	The Lord sat [enthroned] at the flood: and the Lord will sit as King for ever.
019	PSA	029	011	The Lord will give strength unto his people: the Lord will bless his people with peace.
019	PSA	030	001	“A psalm, a song at the dedication of the temple, of David.” I will extol thee, O Lord; for thou hast lifted me up, and hast not suffered my enemies to rejoice over me.
019	PSA	030	002	O Lord my God, I cried loudly unto thee, and thou hast healed me.
019	PSA	030	003	O Lord, thou hast brought up from the nether world my soul: thou hast kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.
019	PSA	030	004	Sing unto the Lord, O ye his pious ones, and give thanks to the memorial of his holiness.
019	PSA	030	005	For his anger is momentary, [but] life is in his favor: in the evening [cometh] weeping to stay for a night, but in the morning, there is joyful song.
019	PSA	030	006	And I had said indeed in my prosperity, I shall never be moved.
019	PSA	030	007	Lord, by thy favor hadst thou caused my mountain to stand in strength: thou didst hide thy face, [and] I was terrified.
019	PSA	030	008	Unto thee, O Lord, will I call; and unto the Lord will I make supplication.
019	PSA	030	009	What profit is there in my blood, when I go down to the grave? Shall the dust thank thee? shall it announce thy truth?
019	PSA	030	010	Hear, O Lord, and be gracious unto me: Lord, be thou a helper unto me.
019	PSA	030	011	Thou hast changed my mourning into dancing for me; thou hast loosened my sack-cloth, and girded me with joy.
019	PSA	030	012	To the end that my glorious soul may sing praise to thee, and never be silent. O Lord my God, for ever will I give thanks unto thee.
019	PSA	031	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David.” In thee, O Lord, do I put my trust; Oh that I may never be put to shame: through thy righteousness do thou release me.
019	PSA	031	002	Bend unto me thy ear; speedily deliver me: be thou unto me as a rock of protection, as a mountain strong-hold to save me.
019	PSA	031	003	For my rock and my stronghold art thou; and for the sake of thy name lead me, and guide me.
019	PSA	031	004	Draw me out of the net which they have laid secretly for me; for thou art my protection.
019	PSA	031	005	Into thy hand do I commit my spirit: thou redeemest me, O Lord, the God of truth.
019	PSA	031	006	I hate those that depend on lying vanities; but I trust indeed in the Lord.
019	PSA	031	007	I will be glad and rejoice in thy kindness; because thou hast seen my misery; thou hast taken cognizance of the distresses of my soul;
019	PSA	031	008	And thou hast not surrendered me into the hand of the enemy: thou hast caused my feet to stand on an ample space.
019	PSA	031	009	Be gracious unto me, O Lord, for I am in distress; my eye is consumed through vexation—my soul [too] and my body.
019	PSA	031	010	For my life is spent with sorrow, and my years with sighing, my strength faileth because of my iniquity, and my bones are consumed.
019	PSA	031	011	Because of all my assailants am I become a reproach, and unto my neighbors greatly so, and a terror to my acquaintance, those that see me abroad flee away from me.
019	PSA	031	012	I am forgotten as a dead man out of the heart: I am become like a perishable vessel.
019	PSA	031	013	For I have heard the slandering of many; terror was on every side, while they took counsel together against me: to take away my life did they purpose.
019	PSA	031	014	But I trusted well in thee, O Lord: I said, Thou art my God.
019	PSA	031	015	In thy hand are my destinies: deliver me from the hand of my enemies, and from my persecutors.
019	PSA	031	016	Let thy face shine upon thy servant: save me through thy kindness.
019	PSA	031	017	O Lord, let me not be put to shame; for I have called on thee: let the wicked be put to shame, let them be silent, [passing] to the nether world.
019	PSA	031	018	Let the lying lips be made dumb, which speak hard things against the righteous, with pride and contempt.
019	PSA	031	019	Oh how great is thy goodness, which thou hast treasured up for those that fear thee; which thou hast wrought for those that trust in thee before the sons of men!
019	PSA	031	020	Thou wilt conceal them in the secret of thy presence from the conspiracy of men: thou wilt keep them secretly in a pavilion from the strife of tongues.
019	PSA	031	021	Blessed be the Lord: for he hath shown me his kindness wonderfully in a beleaguered city.
019	PSA	031	022	And yet had I said in my despondency, I am cut off from before thy eyes: nevertheless thou didst hear the voice of my supplications when I cried loudly unto thee.
019	PSA	031	023	Oh love the Lord, all ye his pious ones: the Lord preserveth the faithful, and recompenses the presumption of him that acteth proudly.
019	PSA	031	024	Be strong, and let your heart be of good courage, all ye that hope in the Lord.
019	PSA	032	001	“Of David: a Maskil.” Happy is he whose transgression is forgiven, whose sin is covered.
019	PSA	032	002	Happy is the man unto whom the Lord imputeth not iniquity, and in whose spirit there is no guile.
019	PSA	032	003	When I kept silence, my bones wasted away through my crying all the day.
019	PSA	032	004	For by day and night lay thy hand heavily upon me: my [life's] moisture hath been changed through the droughts of summer. (Selah)
019	PSA	032	005	My sin do I ever acknowledge unto thee, and my iniquity have I not covered up. I said, I will make confession because of my transgressions unto the Lord: and thou truly forgavest the iniquity of my sin. (Selah)
019	PSA	032	006	For this shall every pious one pray unto thee in a time when thou mayest be found: surely [then] when great waters overflow, they shall never reach unto him.
019	PSA	032	007	Thou art my hiding-place; from distress wilt thou preserve me; with songs of deliverance wilt thou encompass me. (Selah)
019	PSA	032	008	I will instruct thee and I will teach thee concerning the way which thou oughtest to go: I will counsel thee with my eye.
019	PSA	032	009	Be ye not like the horse, or like the mule, who hath no understanding; who must be held in with bit and bridle, his ornament, lest he come near unto thee.
019	PSA	032	010	Many are the pains of the wicked; but him that trusteth in the Lord will he encompass with kindness.
019	PSA	032	011	Rejoice in the Lord, and be glad, ye righteous: and shout for joy, all ye that are upright in heart.
019	PSA	033	001	Be joyful, O ye righteous, in the Lord; [for] unto the righteous praise is comely.
019	PSA	033	002	Give thanks unto the Lord with the harp: with the ten-stringed psaltery do ye sing [praises] unto him.
019	PSA	033	003	Sing unto him a new song; play beautifully amidst a triumphant shout.
019	PSA	033	004	For the word of the Lord is upright; and all his works [are done] in truth.
019	PSA	033	005	He loveth righteousness and justice: the earth is full of the kindness of the Lord.
019	PSA	033	006	By the word of the Lord were the heavens made; and by the breath of his mouth all their host.
019	PSA	033	007	He gathereth together like heaps the waters of the sea: he layeth up in store-houses the depths [of the sea].
019	PSA	033	008	Let all the earth fear the Lord: of him stand in awe all the inhabitants of the world.
019	PSA	033	009	For he spoke, and it came into being: he commanded, and it stood fast.
019	PSA	033	010	The Lord frustrateth the resolves of the nations: he bringeth to nought the thoughts of the people.
019	PSA	033	011	The counsel of the Lord will stand for ever, the thoughts of his heart from generation to generation.
019	PSA	033	012	Happy is the nation whose God is the Lord, the people whom he hath chosen for himself as a heritage.
019	PSA	033	013	The Lord looketh from heaven; he seeth all the sons of men.
019	PSA	033	014	From the place of his habitation he directeth his view upon all the inhabitants of the earth;
019	PSA	033	015	He fashioneth their hearts altogether; he hath regard to all their works.
019	PSA	033	016	The king is not saved by the multitude of an army: a mighty man is not delivered by much strength.
019	PSA	033	017	Vain is the horse for victory: nor shall he deliver any by the greatness of his strength.
019	PSA	033	018	Behold, the eye of the Lord is upon those that fear him, upon those that hope for his kindness.
019	PSA	033	019	To deliver from death their soul, and to keep them alive in famine.
019	PSA	033	020	Our soul waiteth for the Lord: our help and our shield is he.
019	PSA	033	021	For in him shall our heart rejoice: because in his holy name have we trusted.
019	PSA	033	022	Let thy kindness, O Lord, be upon us, even as we hope in thee.
019	PSA	034	001	“By David, when he disguised his reason before Abimelech, who drove him away, and he departed.” I will bless the Lord at all times: continually shall his praise be in my mouth.
019	PSA	034	002	My soul shall make her boast in the Lord: the humble shall hear it, and be rejoiced.
019	PSA	034	003	Oh magnify the Lord with me, and let us exalt his name together.
019	PSA	034	004	I sought the Lord, and he answered me, and from all that I dreaded did he deliver me.
019	PSA	034	005	They [who] looked unto him, were indeed enlightened, and their faces were not put to the blush.
019	PSA	034	006	This poor man cried, and the Lord heard him, and out of all his distresses did he save him.
019	PSA	034	007	The angel of the Lord encampeth round about those who fear him, and delivereth them.
019	PSA	034	008	Experience and see that the Lord is good: happy is the man that trusteth in him.
019	PSA	034	009	Oh fear the Lord, ye his saints: for there is no want to those who fear him.
019	PSA	034	010	The young lions do lack, and suffer hunger; but those who seek the Lord shall not want any good.
019	PSA	034	011	Come, ye children, hearken unto me: the fear of the Lord will I teach you.
019	PSA	034	012	Who is the man that desireth life, loveth [many] days, that he may see happiness?
019	PSA	034	013	Guard thy tongue from evil, and thy lips from speaking deceit.
019	PSA	034	014	Depart from evil, and do good; seek peace, and pursue it.
019	PSA	034	015	The eyes of the Lord are directed unto the righteous, and his ears unto their cry.
019	PSA	034	016	[But] the anger of the Lord is against those that do evil, to cut off from the earth their remembrance.
019	PSA	034	017	Those cry, and the Lord heareth, and from all their distresses he delivereth them.
019	PSA	034	018	The Lord is nigh unto those that are broken-hearted: and he saveth those that are of a contrite spirit.
019	PSA	034	019	Many are the afflictions of the righteous; but out of them all the Lord ever delivereth him.
019	PSA	034	020	He watcheth all his bones: not one of them is broken.
019	PSA	034	021	The evil will slay the wicked: and they who hate the righteous shall incur guiltiness.
019	PSA	034	022	The Lord redeemeth the soul of his servants: and all that trust in him shall not incur guiltiness.
019	PSA	035	001	“Of David.” Contend, O Lord, with those that contend with me: fight against those that fight against me.
019	PSA	035	002	Take hold of shield and buckler, and rise up for my help.
019	PSA	035	003	And draw out the spear, and step in against my pursuers; say unto my soul, I am thy salvation.
019	PSA	035	004	Let those be put to shame and be confounded that seek after my life: let those be turned backward and be made to blush, that devise unhappiness for me.
019	PSA	035	005	Let them be as chaff before the wind; and may the angel of the Lord cast them forth.
019	PSA	035	006	May their way be dark and slippery: and may the angel of the Lord pursue them.
019	PSA	035	007	For without cause have they hidden for me their net in a pit, without cause have they dug [pit-falls] against my life.
019	PSA	035	008	May then destruction come upon each of them at unawares; and may his net that he hath hidden catch himself: in [utter] destruction let him fall therein.
019	PSA	035	009	But my soul shall exult in the Lord: she shall be glad through his salvation.
019	PSA	035	010	All my bones will say, Lord, who is like unto thee, who deliverest the poor from him that is too strong for him, yea, the poor and the needy from him that robbeth him?
019	PSA	035	011	There rise up witnesses of violence; concerning what I know not they question me.
019	PSA	035	012	They recompense me with evil in place of good, [bringing] bereavement on my soul.
019	PSA	035	013	But as for me, when they were sick, my clothing was sackcloth: I afflicted with fasting my soul, and my prayer returned into my own bosom.
019	PSA	035	014	As though he had been to me a friend or a brother did I walk about: as one that mourneth for a mother did I sorrowfully bend down my head.
019	PSA	035	015	But in my downfall they rejoiced, and gathered themselves together; there gathered themselves together against me abject wretches, whom I knew not; they did tear me, and ceased not:
019	PSA	035	016	With hypocritical babbling mockers, they gnashed upon me with their teeth.
019	PSA	035	017	O Lord, how long wilt thou look on? rescue my soul from their destructions, from the young lions my solitary spirit.
019	PSA	035	018	I will thank thee in the great assembly: among a mighty people will I praise thee.
019	PSA	035	019	Let not rejoice over me those that are my enemies wrongfully: [nor] let those who hate me without cause wink with the eye.
019	PSA	035	020	For they speak not peace; but against the quiet in the land they devise deceitful words.
019	PSA	035	021	Yea, they opened wide against me their mouth; they said, Aha, aha, our eye hath seen it.
019	PSA	035	022	Thou hast seen it, O Lord! remain not silent: O Lord, be not far from me.
019	PSA	035	023	Arouse thyself, and awake to do me justice, my God and my Lord, unto my cause.
019	PSA	035	024	Judge me according to thy righteousness, O Lord my God; and let them not rejoice over me.
019	PSA	035	025	Let them not say in their heart, Aha, [this is the wish of] our soul: let them not say, We have swallowed him up.
019	PSA	035	026	Let those be made ashamed and put to the blush together that rejoice at my mishap; let them be clothed with shame and confusion that magnify themselves above me.
019	PSA	035	027	Let those shout, and rejoice, that desire my righteousness: yea, let them say continually, Great is the Lord, who desireth the welfare of his servant.
019	PSA	035	028	And my tongue shall speak of thy righteousness, all the day of thy praise.
019	PSA	036	001	“To the chief musician, by the servant of the Lord, by David.” Saith vice itself to the wicked—so I feel it within my heart— that he should have no dread of God before his eyes.
019	PSA	036	002	For he flattereth himself in his own eyes [too much] to find out his iniquity to hate it.
019	PSA	036	003	The words of his mouth are wickedness and deceit: he hath left off to be wise, to do good.
019	PSA	036	004	He deviseth wickedness upon his couch; he placeth himself on a way that is not good; evil he despiseth not.
019	PSA	036	005	O Lord, into the heavens reacheth thy kindness, thy faithfulness even into the skies.
019	PSA	036	006	Thy righteousness is like the mountains of God; thy acts of justice like the great deep: man and beast dost thou ever help, O Lord.
019	PSA	036	007	How precious is thy kindness, O God! And the children of men that seek shelter under the shadow of thy wings, —
019	PSA	036	008	These will be abundantly satisfied with the fatness of thy house; and of the stream of thy delights wilt thou give them to drink.
019	PSA	036	009	For with thee is the source of life: in thy light shall we see light.
019	PSA	036	010	Draw down continuously thy kindness unto those that acknowledge thee; and thy righteousness to the upright in heart.
019	PSA	036	011	Let not come against me the foot of pride, and let not the hand of the wicked chase me off.
019	PSA	036	012	There are fallen the workers of wickedness: they are thrust down, and shall not be able to rise.
019	PSA	037	001	“Of David.” Do not fret thyself because of the evil-doers, neither be thou envious against the workers of iniquity.
019	PSA	037	002	For like the grass they shall soon be mowed down, and like the green herb shall they wither.
019	PSA	037	003	Trust in the Lord, and do good; dwell in the land, and feed [thyself] with truthfulness.
019	PSA	037	004	And delight thyself in the Lord, and he will give thee the wishes of thy heart.
019	PSA	037	005	Commit thy way unto the Lord, and trust in him: and he will accomplish it.
019	PSA	037	006	And he will bring forth as the light thy righteousness, and the justice of thy [cause] as the noonday.
019	PSA	037	007	Be silent before the Lord, and wait patiently for him: fret not thyself because of him who prospereth in his way, because of the man who practices wicked devices.
019	PSA	037	008	Cease from anger, and forsake wrath: fret not thyself in any wise to do evil.
019	PSA	037	009	For evil-doers shall be cut off; but those that wait upon the Lord, these—shall truly inherit the land.
019	PSA	037	010	For yet but for a little while, and the wicked shall be no more: yea, thou wilt look carefully at his place, and he shall not be there.
019	PSA	037	011	But the meek shall inherit the land, and shall delight themselves because of the abundance of peace.
019	PSA	037	012	The wicked purposeth evil against the just, and gnasheth against him with his teeth.
019	PSA	037	013	The Lord will laugh at him; for he seeth that his day is coming.
019	PSA	037	014	The wicked have drawn out the sword, and have bent their bow, to cause the poor and needy to fall, and to slaughter such as are of an upright course [of life].
019	PSA	037	015	[But] their sword shall enter into their own heart, and their bows shall be broken.
019	PSA	037	016	Better is the little that the righteous hath, than the great riches of many wicked.
019	PSA	037	017	For the arms of the wicked shall be broken: but the upholder of the righteous is the Lord.
019	PSA	037	018	The Lord regardeth the days of the upright: and their inheritance shall endure for ever.
019	PSA	037	019	They shall not be made ashamed in the time of unhappiness; and in the days of famine shall they be satisfied.
019	PSA	037	020	But the wicked shall perish, and the enemies of the Lord shall be as the beauty of the meadow: they pass away; in smoke they pass away.
019	PSA	037	021	The wicked borroweth, and repayeth not; but the righteous is beneficent, and giveth.
019	PSA	037	022	For those blessed of him shall inherit the land; and those cursed of him shall be cut off.
019	PSA	037	023	By the Lord are the steps of the righteous man established; and he findeth pleasure in his course [of life].
019	PSA	037	024	Though he fall, he shall not be utterly cast down; for the Lord upholdeth his hand.
019	PSA	037	025	I have been young, and I am also grown old: yet have I never seen the righteous forsaken, nor his seed seeking for bread.
019	PSA	037	026	He is all the time beneficent, and lendeth: and his seed will be for a blessing.
019	PSA	037	027	Depart from evil, and do good; and dwell for evermore.
019	PSA	037	028	For the Lord loveth justice, and never forsaketh his pious servants: they are for ever preserved; but the seed of the wicked will be cut off.
019	PSA	037	029	The righteous shall inherit the land, and dwell for ever therein.
019	PSA	037	030	The mouth of the righteous uttereth wisdom, and his tongue speaketh what is just.
019	PSA	037	031	The law of his God is in his heart: none of his steps shall slip.
019	PSA	037	032	The wicked looketh out for the righteous, and seeketh to slay him.
019	PSA	037	033	The Lord will not leave him in his hand, and will not condemn him when he is judged.
019	PSA	037	034	Wait on the Lord, and keep his way, and he will exalt thee to inherit the land: when the wicked are cut off, shalt thou look on.
019	PSA	037	035	I have seen the wicked terrible in power, and striking root like a green tree in its native soil.
019	PSA	037	036	Yet he passed away, and, lo, he was no more: and I sought him, but he could not be found.
019	PSA	037	037	Observe the perfect man, and behold the upright; for there is a [happy] future for the man of peace.
019	PSA	037	038	But the transgressors are destroyed together: the future of the wicked is cut off.
019	PSA	037	039	And the salvation of the righteous is from the Lord: he is their strong-hold in the time of distress.
019	PSA	037	040	And the Lord helpeth them, and delivereth them; he will deliver them from the wicked, and save them; because they have put their trust in him.
019	PSA	038	001	“A psalm of David, to bring to remembrance.” O Lord, correct me not in thy wrath, nor chastise me in thy fury.
019	PSA	038	002	For thy arrows have penetrated into me, and thy hand presseth down upon me.
019	PSA	038	003	There is no soundness in my flesh because of thy indignation: there is no peace in my bones because of my sin.
019	PSA	038	004	For my iniquities are passed over my head, as a heavy burden are they too heavy for me.
019	PSA	038	005	Foul, corrupt are my bruises because of my folly.
019	PSA	038	006	I am bent double; I am bowed down to the utmost; all the day long I go about full of grief.
019	PSA	038	007	For my loins are filled with a burning disease, and there is no soundness in my flesh.
019	PSA	038	008	I am made faint and crushed to the utmost; I cry aloud because of the groaning of my heart.
019	PSA	038	009	Lord, before thee is all my longing; and my sighing is from thee not hidden.
019	PSA	038	010	My heart is restless, my strength hath left me; and the light of my eyes—that also is no more with me.
019	PSA	038	011	My lovers and my friends stand aloof from my plague; and my kinsmen stand afar off.
019	PSA	038	012	They also that seek after my life lay snares; and they that wish for my mishap speak wicked falsehoods; and deceits do they devise all the day long.
019	PSA	038	013	But I, as a deaf man, hear not; and I am as a dumb man that cannot open his mouth.
019	PSA	038	014	Thus am I as a man that heareth not, and in whose mouth are no words of defence.
019	PSA	038	015	For in thee, O Lord, do I hope: thou wilt answer, O Lord my God.
019	PSA	038	016	For I said, Perhaps they might rejoice over me: when my foot slippeth, they might magnify themselves over me.
019	PSA	038	017	For I am prepared for [my] downfall, and my pain is continually before me.
019	PSA	038	018	For I will tell of my iniquity; I will be grieved because of my sin.
019	PSA	038	019	But my enemies are strong in life; and numerous are those that hate me wrongfully;
019	PSA	038	020	They also that repay [me] evil in lieu of good; they hate me bitterly because I pursue what is good.
019	PSA	038	021	Forsake me not, O Lord: O my God, be not far from me.
019	PSA	038	022	Make haste to help me, O Lord, my salvation.
019	PSA	039	001	“To the chief musician, to Jeduthun, a psalm of David.” I said, I will guard my ways, that I sin not with my tongue: I will guard my mouth with a muzzle, while the wicked is before me.
019	PSA	039	002	I was dumb in deep silence, I was quite still, even from [speaking] good; but my pain was greatly excited;
019	PSA	039	003	My heart was hot within me, in my self-communing there burnt a fire: [then] spoke I with my tongue,
019	PSA	039	004	Let me know, O Lord, my end, and the measure of my days, what it is: I wish to know when I shall cease to be.
019	PSA	039	005	Behold, measured out with the span hast thou made my days; and my whole duration is nothing before thee: yea, as nothing but vanity doth every man stand here. (Selah)
019	PSA	039	006	As nothing but a shadowy image doth man walk about, yea, for vanity only do all make a noise: he heapeth up his gains, and knoweth not who shall gather them.
019	PSA	039	007	And now, what shall I wait for, O Lord? my hope is in thee.
019	PSA	039	008	From all my transgressions deliver thou me: render me not the object of reproach of the worthless.
019	PSA	039	009	I was dumb, I opened not my mouth; because thou hadst done it.
019	PSA	039	010	Remove thou thy plague away from me: from the blows of thy hand am I consumed.
019	PSA	039	011	When thou with corrections chastisest man for iniquity, thou causest his excellence to melt away as [if eaten by] the moth: yea, nothing but vanity is every man. (Selah)
019	PSA	039	012	Hear my prayer, O Lord, and give ear unto my cry; be not silent at my tears; for a stranger am I with thee, a sojourner, like all my fathers.
019	PSA	039	013	Leave off from me, that I may recover strength, before I go hence, and am no more.
019	PSA	040	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David.” I had waited patiently for the Lord, when he inclined himself unto me, and heard my cry.
019	PSA	040	002	And he brought me up out of the noiseful deep, out of the miry clay, and he set up my feet upon a rock, making firm my steps.
019	PSA	040	003	And he placed in my mouth a new song, a praise unto our God: many will see it, and fear; and they will trust in the Lord.
019	PSA	040	004	Happy is the man that maketh the Lord his trust, and turneth not unto the proud, nor such as stray aside unto lies.
019	PSA	040	005	Many things hast thou done, O Lord my God; thy wonderful deeds and thy thoughts toward us—there is none to be compared unto thee—will I tell and speak of, [though] they are too numerous to be counted.
019	PSA	040	006	Sacrifice and meat-offering thou desirest not—ears hast thou hollowed out unto me—burnt-offering and sin-offering thou demandest not.
019	PSA	040	007	Then said I, Lo, I come: in the roll of the book it is written down for me;
019	PSA	040	008	To fulfill thy will, O my God, do I desire; and thy law is within my heart.
019	PSA	040	009	I announce [thy] righteousness in the great assembly: lo, I will not refrain my lips, O Lord, thou well knowest it.
019	PSA	040	010	Thy righteousness have I never hidden within my heart; thy faithfulness and thy salvation have I spoken of openly: I have not concealed thy kindness and thy truth before the great assembly.
019	PSA	040	011	Do thou, O Lord, not withhold thy mercies from me: let thy kindness and thy truth continually watch over me.
019	PSA	040	012	For evils without number have compassed me about; my iniquities have overtaken me, so that I am not able to see: they are more numerous than the hairs of my head; and my courage hath forsaken me.
019	PSA	040	013	Be pleased, O Lord, to deliver me; O Lord, hasten to my help.
019	PSA	040	014	May those be made ashamed and put to the blush together that seek after my soul to take her away: let them be driven backward and be confounded, that wish for my mishap.
019	PSA	040	015	May they be astonished in consequence of their shame that say unto me, Aha, aha!
019	PSA	040	016	[But] may all those that seek thee be glad and rejoice in thee: may they say continually, The Lord be magnified, —those that love thy salvation.
019	PSA	040	017	But though I be poor and needy, the Lord will think of me: my help and my deliverer art thou: O my God, delay not.
019	PSA	041	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David.” Happy is he that careth for the poor: on the day of evil will the Lord deliver him.
019	PSA	041	002	The Lord will preserve him, and keep him alive; he shall be made happy on the earth: and thou wilt not deliver him unto the revengeful desire of his enemies.
019	PSA	041	003	The Lord will sustain him upon the bed of painful disease: thou changest all his couch in his sickness.
019	PSA	041	004	I said, Lord, be gracious unto me: heal my soul; for I have sinned against thee.
019	PSA	041	005	My enemies speak evil of me, When will he die, and his name perish?
019	PSA	041	006	And if he come to see [me], he speaketh falsely: his heart gathereth wickedness to itself; he goeth abroad [and] speaketh it.
019	PSA	041	007	Altogether whisper against me all that hate me: against me do they devise my injury.
019	PSA	041	008	“His godless deed [say they] is poured out over him: as he lieth there he will never more rise up again.”
019	PSA	041	009	Yea, even the man that should have sought my welfare, in whom I trusted, who eateth my bread, hath lifted up his heel against me.
019	PSA	041	010	But thou, O Lord, be gracious unto me, and raise me up, that I may requite it unto them.
019	PSA	041	011	By this do I know that thou art pleased with me, that my enemy doth not triumph over me.
019	PSA	041	012	But as for me, thou upholdest me in my integrity, and placest me before thy presence for ever.
019	PSA	041	013	Blessed be the Lord the God of Israel from everlasting, and to everlasting. Amen, and Amen. BEGIM
019	PSA	042	001	BOOK SECOND: “To the chief musician, a Maskil, for the sons of Korach.” As a hart panteth after brooks of water, so panteth my soul after thee, O God.
019	PSA	042	002	My soul thirsteth for God, for the living God: when shall I go [again] and be seen in the presence of God?
019	PSA	042	003	My tears have been my food day and night; because men say unto me all the day, Where is thy God?
019	PSA	042	004	These things will I remember, and pour out my soul in me: how I was wont to pass along amidst the multitude, journeying with them as a pilgrim to the house of God, with the voice of joyful song and thanksgiving, among the festive throng.
019	PSA	042	005	Why art thou cast down, O my soul, and disquieted in me? Hope thou in God; for I shall yet thank him, because of the salvation of his countenance.
019	PSA	042	006	O my God, my soul is cast down within me: therefore will I remember thee from the land of the Jordan, and from the peaks of Chermon, from the low mount.
019	PSA	042	007	Deep calleth unto deep at the noise of thy waterfalls: all thy waves and thy billows have passed over me.
019	PSA	042	008	In the daytime the Lord will command his kindness, and in the night his song shall be with me, as a prayer unto the God of my life.
019	PSA	042	009	I will say unto God, my rock, why hast thou forgotten me? why must I walk grieved, under the oppression of the enemy?
019	PSA	042	010	It is as death in my bones, when my assailants reproach me; when they say unto me all the day, Where is thy God?
019	PSA	042	011	Why art thou cast down, O my soul? and why art thou disquieted within met? Hope thou in God; for I shall yet thank him, the salvation of my countenance, and my God.
019	PSA	043	001	Judge me, O God, and plead my cause against an ungodly nation: from the deceitful and unjust man do thou deliver me.
019	PSA	043	002	For thou art the God of my fortress: why hast thou abandoned me? why must I walk about grieved, under the oppression of the enemy?
019	PSA	043	003	Send thou thy light and thy truth, these shall guide me; they shall bring me unto thy holy mountain, and to thy dwellings:
019	PSA	043	004	That I may go unto the altar of God, unto God the joy of my gladness; and that I may thank thee upon the harp, O God, my God.
019	PSA	043	005	Why art thou cast down, O my soul? and why art thou disquieted within me? Hope thou in God; for I shall yet thank him, the salvation of my countenance, and my God.
019	PSA	044	001	“To the chief musician, for the sons of Korach, a Maskil.” O God, with our ears have we heard, our fathers have told us, deeds which thou hadst done in their days, in times of old.
019	PSA	044	002	Thou, with thy hand, didst indeed drive out nations, and plant them; thou didst ill-treat people, and cause them to spread out.
019	PSA	044	003	For not by their sword did they obtain possession of the land, and their own arm brought them no victory; but thy right hand, and thy arm, and the light of thy countenance, because thou hadst given them thy favor.
019	PSA	044	004	Thou art my King, O God: ordain salvation for Jacob.
019	PSA	044	005	Through thee will we butt down our assailants: through thy name will we tread under foot our opponents.
019	PSA	044	006	For not in my bow will I trust, and my sword shall not help me.
019	PSA	044	007	But thou helpest us against our assailants, and those that hate us thou puttest to shame.
019	PSA	044	008	Of God we boast all the day, and to thy name will we give thanks for ever. (Selah)
019	PSA	044	009	But [now] thou hast cast off, and put us to the blush, and goest not forth with our armies.
019	PSA	044	010	Thou causest us to turn back from before our assailant: and they who hate us take spoil for themselves.
019	PSA	044	011	Thou givest us up like sheep for food, and among the nations hast thou dispersed us.
019	PSA	044	012	Thou sellest thy people for no value, and acquirest no gain by their price.
019	PSA	044	013	Thou renderest us a reproach to our neighbors, a scorn and a derision to those that are round about us.
019	PSA	044	014	Thou renderest us a by-word among the nations, a shaking of the head among the people.
019	PSA	044	015	All the day is my disgrace before me, and the shame of my face covereth me;
019	PSA	044	016	Because of the voice of him that reproacheth and blasphemeth; by reason of the enemy and him that seeketh vengeance.
019	PSA	044	017	All this is come over us, yet have we not forgotten thee; nor have we dealt falsely by thy covenant;
019	PSA	044	018	Our heart is not moved backward, nor hath our step turned aside from thy path:
019	PSA	044	019	Even when thou didst crush us in the abode of monsters, and cover us with the shadow of death.
019	PSA	044	020	If we had forgotten the name of our God, or spread forth our hands to a strange God:
019	PSA	044	021	Would not God search out this? for he knoweth the secrets of the heart.
019	PSA	044	022	But for thy sake are we slain all the day; we are counted as flocks [destined] for slaughter.
019	PSA	044	023	Awake, wherefore wilt thou sleep, O Lord? arise, abandon us not for ever.
019	PSA	044	024	Wherefore wilt thou hide thy face, wilt thou forget our misery, and our oppression?
019	PSA	044	025	For our soul is bowed down to the dust; our body cleaveth unto the earth.
019	PSA	044	026	Arise unto our help, and redeem us for the sake of thy kindness.
019	PSA	045	001	“To the chief musician upon Shoshannim, by the sons of Korach, a Maskil, a song of love.” My heart swelleth with a good speech; I say, “My works shall be for the king:” my tongue is the pen of a ready writer.
019	PSA	045	002	Thou art more fair than the children of men; grace is poured out over thy lips: therefore hath God blessed thee for ever.
019	PSA	045	003	Gird thy sword upon the thigh, O mighty one, [it is] thy glory and thy majesty;
019	PSA	045	004	Yea, it is thy majesty: be prosperous, ride along for the cause of truth and meekness and righteousness; and fearful things shall thy right hand teach thee.
019	PSA	045	005	Thy sharpened arrows—people will fall down beneath thee—[will enter] into the heart of the king's enemies.
019	PSA	045	006	Thy throne, given of God, endureth for ever and ever: the sceptre of equity is the sceptre of thy kingdom.
019	PSA	045	007	Thou lovest righteousness, and hatest wickedness: therefore hath God, thy God, anointed thee with the oil of gladness above thy associates.
019	PSA	045	008	Of myrrh, and aloes, and cassia are [fragrant] all thy garments: out of palaces of ivory have they made thee joyful with the sound of music.
019	PSA	045	009	Kings' daughters are among those dear to thee: the queen standeth on thy right hand in fine gold of Ophir.
019	PSA	045	010	Hearken, O daughter, and look, and incline thy ear, and forget thy own people, and thy father's house:
019	PSA	045	011	Then will the king long for thy beauty; for he is thy Lord; and bow thyself to him.
019	PSA	045	012	And the daughter of Tyre shall be there with a gift: the rich among the people shall entreat thy favor.
019	PSA	045	013	All gloriously attired awaiteth the king's daughter in the inner chamber: of wrought gold is her garment.
019	PSA	045	014	In embroidered clothes will she be brought unto the king: virgins that follow her, her companions, are brought unto thee.
019	PSA	045	015	They are led forth with rejoicings and gladness, they enter into the palace of the king.
019	PSA	045	016	Instead of thy fathers shall be thy children: thou wilt appoint them as princes in all the land.
019	PSA	045	017	I will make thy name to be remembered in all generations: therefore shall the people praise thee for ever and ever.
019	PSA	046	001	“To the chief musician: by the sons of Korach, upon 'Alamoth, a song.” God is our protection and strength, a help in distresses, very readily found.
019	PSA	046	002	Therefore will we not fear, even when the earth is transformed, and when mountains are moved into the heart of the seas;
019	PSA	046	003	[When] the waters thereof roar and foam, when mountains quake before his majesty. (Selah)
019	PSA	046	004	[There] is a river, its rivulets cause to rejoice the city of God, the sanctuary of the dwellings of the Most High.
019	PSA	046	005	God is in her midst; she shall not be moved: God will ever help her, at the dawning of [her] morning.
019	PSA	046	006	Nations rage, kingdoms are moved: he letteth his voice be heard, the earth melteth away.
019	PSA	046	007	The Lord of hosts is with us; a defense unto us is the God of Jacob. (Selah)
019	PSA	046	008	Come, look at the deeds of the Lord, who hath made desolations on the earth.
019	PSA	046	009	He causeth wars to cease unto the end of the earth; he breaketh the bow, and cutteth the spear in pieces; he burneth wagons in the fire.
019	PSA	046	010	Leave off, and know that I am God: I will be exalted among the nations, I will be exalted on the earth.
019	PSA	046	011	The Lord of hosts is with us; a defence unto us is the God of Jacob. (Selah)
019	PSA	047	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm for the sons of Korach.” All ye people, clap your hands; shout unto God with the voice of triumph.
019	PSA	047	002	For the Lord is most high, fear-inspiring; he is a great king over all the earth.
019	PSA	047	003	He will subdue people under us, and nations under our feet.
019	PSA	047	004	He will choose for us our inheritance, the excellency of Jacob which he loveth. (Selah)
019	PSA	047	005	God ascendeth amid a triumphal shout, the Lord, amid the sound of the cornet.
019	PSA	047	006	Sing praises to God, sing praises: sing praises unto our King, sing praises.
019	PSA	047	007	For God is King of all the earth: sing ye praises with understanding.
019	PSA	047	008	God reigneth over the nations; God sitteth upon his holy throne.
019	PSA	047	009	The nobles of the people are gathered together, [to be with] the people of the God of Abraham; for unto God belong the shields of the earth: he is greatly exalted.
019	PSA	048	001	“A song and psalm by the sons of Korach.” Great is the Lord, and highly praised in the city of our God, [in] his holy mountain.
019	PSA	048	002	A beautiful district, the joy of the whole earth, is mount Zion, the farthest north, the city of the great King.
019	PSA	048	003	God is become known in her palaces as a defence.
019	PSA	048	004	For, lo, the kings were assembled, they are passed away together.
019	PSA	048	005	They indeed saw—[and] so they were astonished; they were terrified, they were confounded.
019	PSA	048	006	Trembling seized on them there, pain, as on a woman in travail.
019	PSA	048	007	With the east wind thou breakest the ships of Tharshish.
019	PSA	048	008	As we have heard, so have we seen [it] in the city of the Lord of hosts, in the city of our God: God will establish it for ever. (Selah)
019	PSA	048	009	We have reflected on thy kindness, O God, in the midst of thy temple.
019	PSA	048	010	As thy name is, O God, so is thy praise over the ends of the earth: of righteousness is thy right hand full.
019	PSA	048	011	Let mount Zion rejoice, let the daughters of Judah be glad, because of thy judgments.
019	PSA	048	012	Compass Zion about, and walk round about her; number her towers.
019	PSA	048	013	Direct your mind to her outer wall, mark carefully her palaces: in order that ye may tell it to the latest generation.
019	PSA	048	014	For this One is God, our God for ever and ever: he will be our guide even unto death.
019	PSA	049	001	“To the chief musician, by the sons of Korach, a psalm.” Hear this, all ye people; give ear, all ye inhabitants of the perishable world:
019	PSA	049	002	Both the sons of the low and the sons of the high, rich and needy, altogether.
019	PSA	049	003	My mouth shall speak wisdom; and the meditation of my heart shall be of understanding.
019	PSA	049	004	I will incline my ear to a parable: I will open with the harp my riddle.
019	PSA	049	005	Wherefore should I fear in the days of evil, when the iniquity of my oppressors encompasseth me?—
019	PSA	049	006	Of those that trust in their wealth, and boast themselves of the multitude of their riches?
019	PSA	049	007	No one can in any wise redeem his brother, nor can he give to God redemption money for himself;
019	PSA	049	008	For the ransom of their soul is too costly, and it is omitted for ever.
019	PSA	049	009	And should he still live for ever? not see the pit?
019	PSA	049	010	For he must see that wise men die, that together the fool and the brutish person perish and leave to others their wealth.
019	PSA	049	011	Their inward thought is, that their houses are to be for ever, their dwelling-places, from generation to generation; they call them by their own names in [various] countries.
019	PSA	049	012	Nevertheless man in [his] splendor endureth not: he is like the beasts [that] perish.
019	PSA	049	013	This is their way, their folly: yet their posterity will take pleasure in their sayings. (Selah)
019	PSA	049	014	Like flocks are they thrust into the nether world; death will feed them; but the upright shall have dominion over them in that morning, and their form wasteth away in the nether world, [taken away] from their own dwelling.
019	PSA	049	015	But God will redeem my soul from the power of the nether world; for he will take me away. (Selah)
019	PSA	049	016	Be not thou afraid when a man becometh rich, when the glory of his house is increased;
019	PSA	049	017	For when he dieth he can take nothing away; his glory will not descend after him.
019	PSA	049	018	For though he bless his soul during his life, and men praise thee, when thou doest well to thyself:
019	PSA	049	019	She shall go to the generation of his fathers, unto eternity will these never see light.
019	PSA	049	020	Man, though in splendor, who understandeth not, is like the beasts that perish. °
019	PSA	050	001	“A psalm of Assaph.” The God of gods, the Lord, speaketh, and calleth the earth, from the rising of the sun unto his setting.
019	PSA	050	002	Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God shineth forth.
019	PSA	050	003	Our God is coming, and will not keep silence: a fire devoureth before him, and round him there rageth a mighty storm.
019	PSA	050	004	He will call to the heavens above, and to the earth, to judge his people.
019	PSA	050	005	“Gather together unto me my pious servants, who make a covenant with me by sacrifice.”
019	PSA	050	006	And the heavens tell of his righteousness; for God is judge himself. (Selah)
019	PSA	050	007	“Hear, O my people, and I will speak; O Israel, and I will testify against thee: God, thy God, am I.
019	PSA	050	008	Not because of thy sacrifices will I reprove thee; and thy burnt-offerings are continually before me.
019	PSA	050	009	I will not take a bullock out of thy house, nor he-goats out of thy folds.
019	PSA	050	010	For mine are all the beasts of the forest, the cattle upon a thousand mountains.
019	PSA	050	011	I know all the fowls of the mountains: whatever moveth on the fields is with me.
019	PSA	050	012	If I were hungry, I would not say it to thee; for mine is the world, and what filleth it.
019	PSA	050	013	Do I eat the flesh of fatted bulls, or drink the blood of he-goats?
019	PSA	050	014	Offer unto God thanksgiving; and pay unto the Most High thy vows;
019	PSA	050	015	And call on me on the day of distress: I will deliver thee, — and so wilt thou glorify me.”
019	PSA	050	016	But unto the wicked God saith, “What hast thou to do to relate my statutes, and why bearest thou my covenant upon thy mouth?
019	PSA	050	017	And yet thou hatest instruction, and castest my words behind thee.
019	PSA	050	018	When thou seest a thief, then art thou pleased with him, and with adulterers hast thou thy portion.
019	PSA	050	019	Thou lettest loose thy mouth with evil, and thy tongue frameth deceit.
019	PSA	050	020	Thou sittest and speakest against thy brother; against thy own mother's son thou utterest slander.
019	PSA	050	021	These things hast thou done, and I kept silence: thou didst ween that I am like thyself; [but] I will reprove thee, and set it in order before thy eyes.”
019	PSA	050	022	Do but reflect on this, ye that forget God, lest I tear [you] in pieces, with none to deliver.
019	PSA	050	023	Whoso offereth thanksgiving glorifieth me: and to him that ordereth his course aright, will I show the salvation of God.
019	PSA	051	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David, When Nathan the prophet came unto him, after he had gone in unto Bath-sheba'.” Be gracious unto me, O God, according to thy kindness: according to the greatness of thy mercies blot out my transgressions.
019	PSA	051	002	Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin.
019	PSA	051	003	For of my transgressions I have full knowledge; and my sin is before me continually.
019	PSA	051	004	To thee, thee only, have I sinned, and what is evil in thy eyes have I done: —in order that thou mightest be righteous when thou speakest, be justified when thou judgest.
019	PSA	051	005	Behold, in iniquity was I brought forth; and in sin did my mother conceive me.
019	PSA	051	006	Behold, thou desirest truth in the inward parts: therefore do thou cause me to know wisdom in the recesses [of the heart].
019	PSA	051	007	Cleanse me from sin with hyssop, and I shall be clean: wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.
019	PSA	051	008	Cause me to hear gladness and joy; that the bones which thou hast crushed may rejoice.
019	PSA	051	009	Hide thy face from my sins, and all my iniquities do thou blot out.
019	PSA	051	010	Create unto me a clean heart, O God; and a firm spirit renew thou within me.
019	PSA	051	011	Cast me not away from thy presence; and thy holy spirit do not take from me.
019	PSA	051	012	Restore unto me the gladness of thy salvation; and with a liberal spirit do thou support me.—
019	PSA	051	013	I will teach transgressors thy ways, and sinners shall return unto thee.
019	PSA	051	014	Deliver me from blood-guiltiness, O God, thou God of my salvation; [that] my tongue may sing aloud of thy righteousness.
019	PSA	051	015	O Lord, open thou my lips, and my mouth shall declare thy praise.
019	PSA	051	016	For thou desirest not sacrifice; else would I give it: in burnt-offering hast thou no delight.
019	PSA	051	017	The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit: a broken and a contrite heart, O God, wilt thou not despise.
019	PSA	051	018	Do good in thy favor unto Zion; build thou the walls of Jerusalem.
019	PSA	051	019	Then wilt thou be pleased with the sacrifices of righteousness, with burnt-offering and entire offering: then shall bullocks be offered upon thy altar.
019	PSA	052	001	“To the chief musician, a Maskil of David, When Doeg the Edomite came and told Saul, and said unto him, David is come to the house of Achimelech.” What vauntest thou thyself of wickedness, O mighty man? the kindness of God endureth all the time.
019	PSA	052	002	Thy tongue deviseth mischiefs, like a sharpened razor, thou worker of deceit.
019	PSA	052	003	Thou lovest evil more than good; falsehood more than speaking righteousness. (Selah)
019	PSA	052	004	Thou lovest all words of destruction, the tongue of deceit.
019	PSA	052	005	[Therefore] God will also destroy thee for ever: he will take thee away, and pluck thee out of his tent, and root thee out of the land of life. (Selah)
019	PSA	052	006	And the righteous shall see it, and they will be afraid, and laugh concerning him:
019	PSA	052	007	“Lo, this is the man that made not God his fortress; but trusted in the abundance of his riches, relied proudly on his mischievous wickedness.”
019	PSA	052	008	But I am like a green olive-tree in the house of God: I trust in the kindness of God for ever and ever.
019	PSA	052	009	I will thank thee for ever, because thou hast done it: and I will wait on thy name, for [it is] good, before thy pious ones.
019	PSA	053	001	“To the chief musician upon Machalath, a Maskil of David.” The worthless fool saith in his heart, There is no God. They are corrupt, and they are abominable [in their] injustice: there is none that doth good.
019	PSA	053	002	God looketh down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there be one intelligent, one who seeketh for God.
019	PSA	053	003	Every one [of them] hath departed [from righteousness]; altogether are they become corrupt: there is none that doth good, no, not one.
019	PSA	053	004	Is there no knowledge in the workers of wickedness? who eat up my people as they eat bread: [while] they do not call on God.
019	PSA	053	005	There were they terrified with terror where there was no terror; for God had scattered the bones of those that encamped against thee: thou didst put them to shame, because God had rejected them.
019	PSA	053	006	Oh that some one might bring the salvation of Israel out of Zion! When God bringeth back the captivity of his people, [then] will Jacob be glad, [and] Israel will rejoice.
019	PSA	054	001	“To the chief musician on Neginoth, a Maskil of David, When the Ziphim came and said to Saul, Behold, David is hiding himself with us.” O God, by thy name save me, and by thy strength grant me justice.
019	PSA	054	002	O God, hear my prayer; give ear to the words of my mouth.
019	PSA	054	003	For strangers [to goodness] are risen up against me, and powerful oppressors seek after my soul: they have not set God before them. (Selah)
019	PSA	054	004	Behold, God is a helper unto me: the Lord is among those that uphold my soul.
019	PSA	054	005	He will cause the evil to return upon those that regard me with envy: in thy truth cut them off.
019	PSA	054	006	I will liberally sacrifice unto thee: I will give thanks unto thy name, O Lord; for it is good.
019	PSA	054	007	For out of all distress hath he delivered me: and my eye hath seen [its desire] on my enemies.
019	PSA	055	001	“To the chief musician on Neginoth, a Maskil of David.” Give ear, O God, to my prayer, and hide not thyself from my supplication.
019	PSA	055	002	Listen unto me, and answer me: I mourn in my grief, and moan;
019	PSA	055	003	Because of the voice of the enemy, because of the oppression of the wicked; for they cast wrong upon me, and in wrath they attack me.
019	PSA	055	004	My heart is sorely pained within me, and the terrors of death are fallen upon me.
019	PSA	055	005	Fearfulness and trembling are come upon me, and shuddering hath covered me.
019	PSA	055	006	And I said, Oh that some one would give me wings like a dove! I would fly away and dwell [quietly].
019	PSA	055	007	Lo, I would flee far away, I would spend my night in the wilderness. (Selah)
019	PSA	055	008	I would prepare hastily a refuge for me from the sweeping wind [and] from storm.
019	PSA	055	009	Destroy, O Lord, divide their tongue; for I have seen violence and strife in the city;
019	PSA	055	010	Day and night do these encompass it upon her walls: and wrong and trouble are in her midst.
019	PSA	055	011	Mischief is in her midst: guile and deceit depart not from her streets.
019	PSA	055	012	For it is not an enemy that reproached me; then I could bear it: not he that hateth me hath magnified himself against me; then I would have hidden myself from him;
019	PSA	055	013	But it is thou, a man my equal, my guide, and my acquaintance;
019	PSA	055	014	So that we took sweet secret counsel together, and walked unto the house of God in tumultuous company.
019	PSA	055	015	Let him dispense death over them; let them go down alive into the nether world; for evil is in their dwelling, in the midst of them.
019	PSA	055	016	I, however, will call on God: and the Lord will save me.
019	PSA	055	017	At evening and morning and noon will I make my complaint and moan: and he heareth my voice.—
019	PSA	055	018	He delivereth my soul in peace from the battle against me; for in multitudes are they [contending] with me.
019	PSA	055	019	God will hear, and humble them—yea, he that sitteth enthroned from the oldest time Selah—those who dread no changes, and fear not God.
019	PSA	055	020	He stretcheth out his hands against those at peace with him: he violateth his covenant.
019	PSA	055	021	The creamy words of his mouth are smooth, yet there is war [in] his heart; his words are softer than oil, yet are they drawn swords.
019	PSA	055	022	Cast thy burden upon the Lord, and he will sustain thee: he will never suffer the righteous to be moved.
019	PSA	055	023	But thou, O God, thou wilt bring them down into the pit of destruction: let not the men of blood and deceit live out half their days; but I will indeed trust in thee.
019	PSA	056	001	“To the chief musician upon Jonath-elem-rechokim, by David, a Michtham, when the Philistines seized him in Gath.” Be gracious unto me, O God; for man longeth to swallow me up; all the time he oppresseth me fighting.
019	PSA	056	002	Those that regard me with envy long to swallow [me] up all the time; for many are they that fight against me, O thou Most High.
019	PSA	056	003	The day [when] I am afraid, I will still trust in thee.
019	PSA	056	004	In God will I praise his word, in God I have put my trust; I will not be afraid: what can flesh do unto me?
019	PSA	056	005	All the day they wrest my words: against me are all their thoughts for evil.
019	PSA	056	006	They come together in troops, they hide themselves, they are those that watch my heels, as though they hoped [to take] my soul.
019	PSA	056	007	Because of their wrong-doing let me escape from them: in anger cast down the people, O God.
019	PSA	056	008	My wanderings hast thou well numbered: put thou my tears into thy bottle; behold, they are numbered by thee.
019	PSA	056	009	Then shall my enemies retire backward on the day when I call [on thee]: this I know—that God is for me.
019	PSA	056	010	In God will I praise the word: in the Lord will I praise the word.
019	PSA	056	011	In God have I put my trust; I will not be afraid: what can man do unto me?
019	PSA	056	012	Upon me, O God, [rest] thy vows: I will pay thanksgiving offerings unto thee.
019	PSA	056	013	For thou hast delivered my soul from death—yea, behold, my feet from slipping, that I may walk before God in the light of the life.
019	PSA	057	001	“To the chief musician, Al-tashcheth, by David, a Michtham, when he fled from Saul, in the cave.” Be gracious unto me, O God, be gracious unto me; for in thee my soul seeketh protection, and under the shadow of thy wings will I seek protection, until the mischief be passed away.
019	PSA	057	002	I will call unto God, the Most High; unto God that accomplisheth [his kindness] on me.
019	PSA	057	003	He will send from heaven, and save me, though he that longeth to swallow me up utter reproach. (Selah) God will send forth his kindness and his truth.
019	PSA	057	004	My soul is in the midst of lions; I lie down [in the midst of] those that send out flames, [those] sons of men, whose teeth are spears and arrows, and whose tongue is a sharpened sword.
019	PSA	057	005	Be thou exalted above the heavens, O God: above all the earth let thy glory be.
019	PSA	057	006	A net have they prepared for my steps; my soul hath been bent down; they have dug before me a pit; they are fallen into the midst thereof. (Selah)
019	PSA	057	007	Firm is my heart, O God, firm is my heart: I will sing and play.
019	PSA	057	008	Awake, my spirit; awake, psaltery and harp: I will wake up the morning-dawn.
019	PSA	057	009	I will thank thee among the people, O Lord: I will sing praises unto thee among the nations.
019	PSA	057	010	For great, even unto the heavens, is thy kindness, and even unto the skies [extendeth] thy truth.
019	PSA	057	011	Be thou exalted above the heavens, O God: above all the earth let thy glory be.
019	PSA	058	001	“To the chief musician Al-tashcheth, by David, a Michtham.” Do you indeed, who are dumb, speak righteously? do ye judge in uprightness, O ye sons of men?
019	PSA	058	002	Even in [your] heart ye work injustice: on the earth do ye weigh out the violence of your hands.
019	PSA	058	003	The wicked are estranged [from goodness] from the womb: those who speak lies go astray from their very birth.
019	PSA	058	004	They have poison like the poison of a serpent: [they are] like the deaf adder that stoppeth her ear;
019	PSA	058	005	Which will not hearken to the voice of conjurers, yea, that of the wisest of all charmers.
019	PSA	058	006	O God, break out their teeth in their mouth: the jaw-teeth of the young lions tear thou out, O Lord.
019	PSA	058	007	Let them melt away as water [which] runneth off: when each one bendeth [his bow to shoot] his arrows, let them be as if cut in pieces.
019	PSA	058	008	As a snail which melteth, let him pass away; like the untimely birth of a woman which hath not seen the sun.
019	PSA	058	009	Before your pots can feel the thorns, will he take them away with a whirlwind, both the green and the burning.
019	PSA	058	010	The righteous will rejoice when he seeth the vengeance: he will bathe his steps in the blood of the wicked.
019	PSA	058	011	So that a man shall say, Verily fruit will come for the righteous: verily there is a God that judgeth on the earth.
019	PSA	059	001	“To the chief musician, Al-tashcheth, by David, a Michtham, when Saul sent, and they watched the house to put him to death.” Deliver me from my enemies, O my God: defend me from them that rise up against me.
019	PSA	059	002	Deliver me from the workers of wickedness, and from men of blood do thou save me.
019	PSA	059	003	For, lo, they lie in wait for my soul, the mighty are gathered in troops against me: not for my transgression, nor for my sin, O Lord.
019	PSA	059	004	Without guilt [in me] they run and make themselves ready: awake, [come] toward me, and behold.
019	PSA	059	005	And thou, O Lord God of hosts, the God of Israel, awake to punish all the nations: be not gracious to any treacherous wicked one. (Selah)
019	PSA	059	006	They will return at evening; they will howl like dogs, and go round about the city.
019	PSA	059	007	Behold, they sputter with their mouth: swords are in their lips; for who, [say they,] doth hear?
019	PSA	059	008	But thou, O Lord, wilt laugh at theme: thou wilt hold in derision all the nations.
019	PSA	059	009	Because of [the enemy's] strength will I wait upon thee; for God is my defence.
019	PSA	059	010	The God who showeth me kindness will go before me: God will let me see [my desire] upon those who regard me with envy.
019	PSA	059	011	Slay them not, that my people may not forget: drive them about by thy power; and bring them down, thou our shield, O Lord.
019	PSA	059	012	The sin of their mouth is the word of their lips: let them be caught through their pride, because of the cursing and lying which they relate.
019	PSA	059	013	Make an end in fury, make an end [of them], that they my be no more, and let them know that God ruleth in Jacob, as far as the ends of the earth. (Selah)
019	PSA	059	014	And they will return in the evening; they will howl like dogs, and go round about the city.
019	PSA	059	015	They will indeed roam about after something to eat, if they be not satisfied, so that they can be at rest.
019	PSA	059	016	But I will truly sing of thy strength; yea, I will sing joyfully in the morning of thy kindness; for thou hast been a defence unto me and a refuge on the day when I was distressed.
019	PSA	059	017	Unto thee, O my strength, will I sing; for God is my defence, the God of my kindness.
019	PSA	060	001	“To the chief musician upon Shushan'eduth, a Michtham of David, to teach, When he fought with Aram-naharayim, and with Aram-zobah, and Joab returned, and smote of Edom in the Salt Valley twelve thousand [men].” O God, thou hast cast us off, thou hast made a breach in us, thou hast been displeased: restore now unto us [thy favor].
019	PSA	060	002	Thou hast caused the earth to quake; thou hast split it: heal her breaches; for she is moved.
019	PSA	060	003	Thou hast caused thy people to see hard things: thou hast made us to drink the wine of confusion.
019	PSA	060	004	Thou hast given to those that fear thee a banner, to elevate themselves, because of the truth. (Selah)
019	PSA	060	005	In order that thy beloved may be delivered: help with thy right hand, and answer me.
019	PSA	060	006	God hath spoken in his holiness: I will exult, I will divide Shechem, and the valley of Succoth will I measure out.
019	PSA	060	007	Mine is Gil'ad, and mine is Menasseh; Ephraim also is the strong-hold of my head; of Judah are my chiefs;
019	PSA	060	008	Moab is my washpot; upon Edom will I cast my shoe: Philistia, triumph thou but over me.
019	PSA	060	009	Who will bring me into the fortified city? who will lead me as far as Edom?
019	PSA	060	010	Behold, it is thou, O God, who hast cast us off; and thou, O God, goest not forth with our armies.
019	PSA	060	011	Give us help against the assailant; for vain is the help of man.
019	PSA	060	012	Through God shall we do valiantly: and he it is that will tread down our assailants.
019	PSA	061	001	“To the chief musician upon Neginah, by David.” Hear, O God, my entreaty; listen to my prayer.
019	PSA	061	002	From the end of the earth will I call unto thee, when my heart is overwhelmed: lead me to the rock that is too high for me.
019	PSA	061	003	For thou hast been a shelter unto me, a strong tower against the enemy.
019	PSA	061	004	Let me sojourn in thy tent to all eternity; let me be sheltered under the covert of thy wings. (Selah)
019	PSA	061	005	For thou, O God, hast truly listened to my vows: thou hast given back the heritage of those that fear thy name.
019	PSA	061	006	Oh, add days unto the king's days: may his years be as of many generations.
019	PSA	061	007	May he abide for ever before God: ordain that kindness and truth may guard him.
019	PSA	061	008	So will I sing praise unto thy name for ever, that I may pay my vows day by day.
019	PSA	062	001	“To the chief musician, upon Jeduthun, a psalm of David.” Only in God my soul trusted in silence: from him cometh my salvation.
019	PSA	062	002	Only he is my rock and my salvation; [he is] my defense: I shall not be greatly moved.
019	PSA	062	003	How long will ye devise mischief against a man? will ye all assault him murderously, as though he were a falling wall, a tottering fence?
019	PSA	062	004	Yea, from his height do they take counsel to cast [him] down; they delight in lies: with their mouth do they bless, but inwardly do they curse. (Selah)
019	PSA	062	005	Yea, in God hope in silence, my soul; for from him is my expectation.
019	PSA	062	006	Only he is my rock and my salvation; [he is] my defence: I shall not be moved.
019	PSA	062	007	With God are my salvation and my glory: the rock of my strength [and] my protection are in God.
019	PSA	062	008	Trust in him at all times, O ye people; pour out before him your heart: God is a protection for us. (Selah)
019	PSA	062	009	Verily nought are the sons of common men, a lie the sons of the great; they must rise in the balance; they are altogether [lighter] than nought.
019	PSA	062	010	Do not put your trust in defrauding, and be not rendered vain through robbery: if riches flourish, set not your heart [upon them].
019	PSA	062	011	Once hath God spoken; [yea,] twice [what] I have heard: that strength belongeth unto God.
019	PSA	062	012	And unto thee, O Lord, belongeth kindness; for thou wilt recompense every man according to his works.
019	PSA	063	001	“A psalm of David, when he was in the wilderness of Judah.” O God, thou art my God; early will I seek thee: my soul thirsteth for thee, my flesh longeth for thee in a dry land, and it is faint without water.
019	PSA	063	002	As I have beheld thee in the sanctuary, seeing thy strength and thy glory;
019	PSA	063	003	Because thy kindness is better than life, my lips shall praise thee:
019	PSA	063	004	Thus will I bless thee while I live; in thy name will I lift up my hands.
019	PSA	063	005	As with fat and marrow will my soul be satisfied; and with tuneful lips shall my mouth praise thee.
019	PSA	063	006	When I remember thee upon my couch, I meditate on thee in the night-watches.
019	PSA	063	007	Because thou hast been a help unto me; and in the shadow of thy wings will I sing rejoicingly.
019	PSA	063	008	My soul cleaveth unto following thee: me thy right hand upholdeth.
