019	PSA	075	001	“To the chief musician, Al-tashcheth, a psalm or song of Asaph.” We give thanks unto thee, O God, we give thanks, and nigh is thy name: men relate thy wondrous deeds.
019	PSA	075	002	“For I will take up a fixed time when I will judge uprightly.
019	PSA	075	003	The earth and all her inhabitants are melting away: I myself establish firmly her pillars.” (Selah)
019	PSA	075	004	I said unto the arrogant, Deal not arrogantly: and to the wicked, Lift not up the horn.
019	PSA	075	005	Lift not up on high your horn, speak not with a stiffly erect neck.
019	PSA	075	006	For neither from the rising [of the sun], nor from [his] setting, nor from the wilderness of mountains [cometh this];
019	PSA	075	007	But God is the judge: he lowereth one, and lifteth up another,
019	PSA	075	008	For there is a cup in the hand of the Lord, and the wine foameth, it is full of mixture: and he poureth out of the same; but its lees they drain, they drink—all the wicked of the earth.
019	PSA	075	009	But I will declare for ever, I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.
019	PSA	075	010	And all the horns of the wicked will I hew off; but the horns of the righteous shall be exalted.
019	PSA	076	001	“To the chief musician on Neginoth, a psalm or song of Assaph.” In Judah hath God been made known: in Israel is his name great.
019	PSA	076	002	And in Salem was his tabernacle made, and his dwelling-place in Zion.
019	PSA	076	003	There broke he the shining arrows of the bow, shield, and sword, and battle. (Selah)
019	PSA	076	004	Thou art more brilliant, more excellent than the mountains [full] of prey.
019	PSA	076	005	Bereft of reason are the stouthearted, they slumber their sleep: and none of the men of might have found [the use of] their hands.
019	PSA	076	006	From thy rebuke, O God of Jacob, lie in deep sleep both chariot and horse.
019	PSA	076	007	Thou—thou art to be feared: and who may stand in thy sight when once thy anger [is kindled]?
019	PSA	076	008	From heaven hast thou caused [thy] sentence to be heard: the earth feared, and became still,
019	PSA	076	009	When God rose to judgment, to save all the lowly of the earth. (Selah)
019	PSA	076	010	For the fury of man shall praise thee: the remainder of the fury wilt thou gird about thee.
019	PSA	076	011	Make vows, and pay [them] unto the Lord your God, all ye that are round about him: let men bring presents unto him that exciteth fear.
019	PSA	076	012	He will cut down the spirit of the powerful: he is terrible to the kings of the earth.
019	PSA	077	001	“To the chief musician on Jeduthun, by Assaph a psalm.” [I lift up] my voice unto God, and I cry; [I lilt up] my voice unto God: do then give ear unto me.
019	PSA	077	002	On the day of my distress I sought the Lord; in the night my hand was stretched out, and did not cease: my soul refused to be comforted.
019	PSA	077	003	I think of God, and moan: I reflect, and my spirit is overwhelmed. (Selah)
019	PSA	077	004	Thou holdest my eyes awake: I am troubled and I cannot speak.
019	PSA	077	005	I think over the days of old, the years of ancient times.
019	PSA	077	006	I call to remembrance my song in the night; with my own heart I reflect: and my spirit maketh diligent search.
019	PSA	077	007	Will the Lord cast me off for ever? and will he never more give his favor again?
019	PSA	077	008	Is his kindness spent for ever? is his promise come to an end for all generations?
019	PSA	077	009	Hath God forgotten to be gracious? or hath he shut up in anger his mercies? (Selah)
019	PSA	077	010	And I said, This shall be my entreaty, [for] the years of the right hand of the Most High.
019	PSA	077	011	I will remember the deeds of the Lord; for I will remember out of ancient times thy wonders.
019	PSA	077	012	I will meditate also of all thy work, and on thy deeds will I reflect.
019	PSA	077	013	O God, in holiness is thy way: where is there a god so great as God?
019	PSA	077	014	Thou art the God that dost wonders: thou hast made known among the people thy strength.
019	PSA	077	015	Thou hast redeemed with [a mighty] arm thy people, the sons of Jacob and Joseph. (Selah)
019	PSA	077	016	The waters saw thee, O God, the waters saw thee; they shook: also the depths trembled.
019	PSA	077	017	The clouds poured out water; the skies sent forth thunder: also thy arrows sped along.
019	PSA	077	018	The voice of thy thunder was in the whirlwind; lightnings gave light to the world; the earth trembled and quaked,
019	PSA	077	019	Through the sea led thy way, and thy path was through mighty waters, and thy footsteps could not be known.
019	PSA	077	020	Thou didst lead like a flock thy people by means of Moses and Aaron.
019	PSA	078	001	“A Maskil of Assaph.” Give ear, O my people, to my instruction: incline thy ear to the words of my mouth.
019	PSA	078	002	I will open with a parable my mouth: I will utter riddles out of ancient times;
019	PSA	078	003	Which we have heard and know, and which our fathers have related unto us.
019	PSA	078	004	We will not conceal them from their children, relating to the latest generation the praises of the Lord, and his strength, and his wonderful deeds which he hath done.
019	PSA	078	005	Yea, he established a testimony in Jacob, and instituted a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, that they should make them known to their children:
019	PSA	078	006	In order that the latest generation might know them, even the children that are to be born; that they may arise and relate them to their children;
019	PSA	078	007	That they may place in God their hope, and not forget the doings of God, but observe his commandments;
019	PSA	078	008	And that they may not be like their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation; a generation that had not directed their heart firmly, and whose spirit was not faithful to God.
019	PSA	078	009	The children of Ephraim, like well-armed archers, that turn round on the day of battle,
019	PSA	078	010	Kept not the covenant of God, and in his law they refused to walk;
019	PSA	078	011	And they forgot his deeds, as also his wonders, which he had permitted them to see.
019	PSA	078	012	In the presence of their fathers did he do wonders, in the land of Egypt, in the fields of Zo'an.
019	PSA	078	013	He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through; and he made the waters stand upright as a wall.
019	PSA	078	014	And he led them with the cloud by day, and all the night with a light of fire.
019	PSA	078	015	He split rocks in the wilderness, and gave them drink as out of the mighty deep.
019	PSA	078	016	And he brought forth running streams out of the rock, and caused water to run down like rivers.
019	PSA	078	017	But they repeated to sin yet more against him, rebelling against the Most High in the desert.
019	PSA	078	018	And they tempted God in their heart, by asking food for their desire.
019	PSA	078	019	Yea, they spoke against God: they said, Will God be able to set in order a table in the wilderness?
019	PSA	078	020	Behold, he smote the rock, so that waters gushed out, and streams overflowed: shall he also be able to give bread? or can he provide flesh for his people?
019	PSA	078	021	Therefore, when the Lord heard this, he became wroth: and a fire was kindled against Jacob, and anger also ascended against Israel,
019	PSA	078	022	Because they had not believed in God, and had not trusted in his salvation.
019	PSA	078	023	Then he ordained the skies from above, and the doors of heaven he opened;
019	PSA	078	024	And he let rain down upon them manna to eat, and the corn of heaven gave he unto them.
019	PSA	078	025	Angels' bread did man eat: he sent them provision to satisfaction.
019	PSA	078	026	He caused an east wind to pass along the heavens; and he led forth by his strength the south wind.
019	PSA	078	027	And he let rain upon them flesh [as plentiful] as the dust, and winged birds like the sand of the sea;
019	PSA	078	028	And he let them fall in the midst of their camp, round about their habitations.
019	PSA	078	029	And they ate, and were greatly satisfied, and what they longed for he brought unto them.
019	PSA	078	030	They were not estranged from their longing, yet was their food in their mouth:
019	PSA	078	031	When the wrath of God ascended against them, and he slew some of the fattest of them, and the young men of Israel did he strike down.
019	PSA	078	032	With all this they sinned again, and believed not in his wonders.
019	PSA	078	033	Therefore he caused their days to come to an end in nought, and their years in dread.
019	PSA	078	034	When he slew them, then did they seek him, and they returned and inquired earnestly after God.
019	PSA	078	035	And they remembered that God was their rock, and the most high God their redeemer.
019	PSA	078	036	Nevertheless they prayed insincerely to him with their mouth, and with their tongue they lied unto him.
019	PSA	078	037	For their heart was not firm with him, and they were not faithful in his covenant.
019	PSA	078	038	But he, being merciful, forgave the iniquity, and destroyed [them] not: yea, many a time turned he his anger away, and did not awaken all his fury.
019	PSA	078	039	And he remembered that they are but flesh, a spirit that passeth away, and returneth not again.
019	PSA	078	040	How oft did they rebel against him in the wilderness, grieve him in the desert!
019	PSA	078	041	Yea, they once more tempted God, and set limits to the Holy One of Israel.
019	PSA	078	042	They remembered not his hand, the day when he ransomed them from the adversary;
019	PSA	078	043	When he displayed in Egypt his signs, and his wonderful tokens in the fields of Zo'an.
019	PSA	078	044	And he changed their rivers into blood; and their running streams, that they could not drink [of them].
019	PSA	078	045	He sent out among them various wild beasts, which devoured them; and frogs, which destroyed them.
019	PSA	078	046	And he gave unto the cricket their products, and their labor unto the locust.
019	PSA	078	047	He slew with hail their vines, and their sycamore-trees with ice-bolts.
019	PSA	078	048	And he surrendered to the hail their cattle, and their herds to the lightning's flashes.
019	PSA	078	049	He let loose against them the fierceness of his anger, wrath and indignation, and distress, a host of angels of misfortune.
019	PSA	078	050	He leveled a path for his anger; he withheld not from death their soul, and their life he surrendered to the pestilence;
019	PSA	078	051	And he smote all the first-born in Egypt; the first of their strength in the tents of Ham;
019	PSA	078	052	But he caused his own people to depart like flocks, and guided them like a drove in the wilderness.
019	PSA	078	053	And he led them in safety, so that they felt no dread; but the sea covered over their enemies.
019	PSA	078	054	And he brought them to his holy territory, even to this mount, which his right hand had acquired.
019	PSA	078	055	And he drove out from before them nations, and divided them by the measuring-line as an inheritance, and he caused to dwell in their tents the tribes of Israel.
019	PSA	078	056	Yet they tempted and rebelled against the most high God, and his testimonies they kept not;
019	PSA	078	057	But swerved aside, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers; they turned about like a deceitful bow.
019	PSA	078	058	And they provoked him to anger with their high-places, and with their graven images they moved him to jealousy.
019	PSA	078	059	God heard this, and he became wroth, and felt greatly disgusted with Israel;
019	PSA	078	060	And he cast off the dwelling at Shiloh, the tabernacle where he had dwelt among men;
019	PSA	078	061	And he gave up his strength unto captivity, and his glory into the adversary's hand.
019	PSA	078	062	And he surrendered his people unto the sword; and with his inheritance was he wroth.
019	PSA	078	063	His young men the fire devoured; and his virgins were not demanded in marriage.
019	PSA	078	064	His priests fell by the sword; and his widows did not weep.
019	PSA	078	065	Then awoke the Lord as one that sleepeth, like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.
019	PSA	078	066	And he smote his enemies backward: a perpetual disgrace on them.
019	PSA	078	067	Yet was he disgusted with the tent of Joseph, and of the tribe of Ephraim he made not choice;
019	PSA	078	068	But he chose the tribe of Judah, the mount Zion which he loved.
019	PSA	078	069	And he built like high [mountains] his sanctuary, like the earth which he hath founded for ever.
019	PSA	078	070	And he made choice of David his servant, and took him from the sheep-folds:
019	PSA	078	071	From following the ewes with young he brought him, to feed Jacob his people, and Israel his inheritance.
019	PSA	078	072	And he fed them according to the integrity of his heart; and by the skilfulness of his hands did he lead them.
019	PSA	079	001	“A psalm of Assaph.” O God! nations have entered into thy heritage; they have profaned thy holy temple; they have rendered Jerusalem heaps of ruins.
019	PSA	079	002	They have given the dead bodies of thy servants as food unto the fowls of the heaven, the flesh of thy pious ones unto the beasts of the earth.
019	PSA	079	003	They have shed their blood like water all round about Jerusalem: and there is no one to bury them.
019	PSA	079	004	We are become a reproach to our neighbors, a scorn and derision to those that are round about us.
019	PSA	079	005	How long, Lord? wilt thou be indignant for ever? shall thy jealousy burn like fire?
019	PSA	079	006	Pour out thy fury over the nations that acknowledge thee not, and over the kingdoms that have not called on thy name.
019	PSA	079	007	For they have devoured Jacob, and laid waste his dwelling-place.
019	PSA	079	008	Oh remember not against us the iniquities of our fathers: make haste, let thy mercies come to our aid; for we are very miserable.
019	PSA	079	009	Help us, O God of our salvation, because of the glory of thy name; and deliver us, and atone for our sins, for the sake of thy name.
019	PSA	079	010	Wherefore shall the nations say, Where is their God? let there be made known among the nations before our eyes, the vengeance for the blood of thy servants which hath been shed.
019	PSA	079	011	Let the sighing of the prisoner come before thee: according to the greatness of thy almighty power preserve thou those that are doomed to death;
019	PSA	079	012	And recompense unto our neighbors sevenfold into their bosom their defiance wherewith they have defied thee, O Lord.
019	PSA	079	013	But we thy people and the flock of thy pasture will give thanks unto thee for ever: from generation to generation will we relate thy praise.
019	PSA	080	001	“To the chief musician upon Shoshannim; an 'Eduth by Assaph; a psalm.” O Shepherd of Israel, give ear, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock; thou that dwellest between the cherubims, shine forth.
019	PSA	080	002	Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Menasseh awaken thy might, and come to our help.
019	PSA	080	003	O God, cause us to return, and let thy countenance shine, that we may be saved.
019	PSA	080	004	O Lord of hosts, how long shall thy anger smoke against the prayer of thy people?
019	PSA	080	005	Thou feedest them with the bread of tears, and givest them tears to drink in great measure.
019	PSA	080	006	Thou renderest us a contest unto our neighbors: and our enemies hold derision among themselves.
019	PSA	080	007	O God of hosts, cause us to return, and let thy countenance shine, that we may be saved.
019	PSA	080	008	A vine didst thou remove out of Egypt: thou drovest out nations, and plantedst it.
019	PSA	080	009	Thou didst clear out a place before it, and it struck its root deeply, and it filled the land.
019	PSA	080	010	Mountains were covered with its shadow, and with its boughs the cedars of God.
019	PSA	080	011	It sent out its tendrils as far as the sea, and unto the river its suckers.
019	PSA	080	012	Wherefore hast thou now broken down its fences, so that all who pass by the way pluck the fruit from it?
019	PSA	080	013	The boar out of the forest doth gnaw at it, and what moveth on the field feedeth on it.
019	PSA	080	014	O God of hosts, return; I pray thee, look down from heaven, and behold, and think of this vine;
019	PSA	080	015	And of the sprout which thy right hand hath planted, and of the branch that thou hast made strong for thyself.
019	PSA	080	016	It is burnt with fire, it is hewn down; because of the rebuke of thy countenance do they perish.
019	PSA	080	017	Let thy hand be over the man of thy right hand, over the son of man whom thou hast made strong for thyself.
019	PSA	080	018	Then will we not swerve from thee: revive us again, and we will call on thy name.
019	PSA	080	019	O Lord God of hosts, cause us to return: let thy countenance shine, that we may be saved.
019	PSA	081	001	“To the chief musician upon Gittith; by Assaph.” Sing aloud unto God our strength: shout joyfully unto the God of Jacob.
019	PSA	081	002	Lift up psalm, and bring hither the timbrel, the pleasant harp with the psaltery.
019	PSA	081	003	Blow on the new moon the cornet, at the time appointed, on the day of our feast.
019	PSA	081	004	For this is a statute for Israel, an ordinance by the God of Jacob.
019	PSA	081	005	As a testimony in Joseph did he ordain it, when he went out over the land of Egypt. The language of one I had not known did I hear.
019	PSA	081	006	I removed from the burden his shoulder: his hands left behind the burden-basket.
019	PSA	081	007	In distress thou didst call, and I delivered thee; I answered thee in the secret of the thunder: I proved thee at the waters of Meribah. (Selah)
019	PSA	081	008	Hear, O my people, and I will give warning unto thee; O Israel, if thou wouldst but hearken unto me!
019	PSA	081	009	There shall not be among thee a foreign God; nor shalt thou bow thyself down to any strange God.
019	PSA	081	010	I am the Lord thy God, who have brought thee up out of the land of Egypt: open wide thy mouth, and I will fill it.
019	PSA	081	011	But my people did not hearken to my voice; and Israel was not willing [to follow] me.
019	PSA	081	012	So I let them go in the stubbornness of their own hearts: and they walked in their own counsels.
019	PSA	081	013	Oh that my people would hearken unto me, that Israel would walk in my ways!
019	PSA	081	014	In a little while would I subdue their enemies, and against their adversaries would I turn my hand.
019	PSA	081	015	The haters of the Lord should offer flattery unto him; but their time should endure for ever.
019	PSA	081	016	And he would feed him with the best of wheat: and out of the rock would I satisfy thee with honey.
019	PSA	082	001	“A psalm of Assaph.” God standeth in the congregation of God, in the midst of judges doth he judge.
019	PSA	082	002	How long will ye judge unjustly, and treat with favor the face of the wicked? (Selah)
019	PSA	082	003	Judge uprightly the poor and fatherless: do justice to the afflicted and indigent.
019	PSA	082	004	Release the poor and needy: deliver them out of the power of the wicked.
019	PSA	082	005	They know not, nor will they understand; in darkness do they walk on: all the foundations of the earth are moved.
019	PSA	082	006	I have indeed said, Ye are gods; and children of the most High are all of you.
019	PSA	082	007	But verily like men shall ye die, and like one of the princes shall ye fall.
019	PSA	082	008	Arise, O God, judge the earth; for thou wilt possess all the nations.
019	PSA	083	001	“A song or psalm of Assaph.” O God, take no rest for thyself: be not silent and keep not still, O God!
019	PSA	083	002	For, lo, thy enemies make a tumult, and they that hate thee have lifted up their head.
019	PSA	083	003	Against thy people they take crafty secret device, and they consult against those whom thou protectest.
019	PSA	083	004	They have said, Come, and let us cut them off from being a nation; and the name of Israel shall be remembered no more.
019	PSA	083	005	For they have consulted cordially together; against thee they make a covenant:
019	PSA	083	006	The tents of Edom, and the Ishmaelites: Moab, and the Hagarenes;
019	PSA	083	007	Gebal, and 'Ammon, and 'Amalek; the Philistines with the inhabitants of Tyre;
019	PSA	083	008	Also Asshur is joined with them; they have become an arm unto the children of Lot. (Selah)
019	PSA	083	009	Do unto them as [unto] Midian; as to Sissera, as to Jabin, at the brook Kishon:
019	PSA	083	010	Who were annihilated at 'En-dor; they became as dung for the ground.
019	PSA	083	011	Render them, their nobles, like 'Oreb, and like Zeeb; yea, like Zebach and like Zalmunna' all their princes;
019	PSA	083	012	Who said, Let us conquer for ourselves the dwellings of God,
019	PSA	083	013	O my God, render them like the thistle-down, like stubble before the wind.
019	PSA	083	014	As the fire burneth up a forest, and as the flame setteth the mountains on fire:
019	PSA	083	015	So pursue them with thy storm, and with thy whirlwind do thou terrify them.
019	PSA	083	016	Fill their faces with shame, that they may seek thy name, O Lord!
019	PSA	083	017	Let them be made ashamed and terrified for ever and aye; yea, let them be put to the blush and perish:
019	PSA	083	018	That they may know that thou, whose name is the Eternal, art by thyself alone, the Most High over all the earth.
019	PSA	084	001	“To the chief musician upon Gittith, by the sons of Korach, a psalm.” How lovely are thy dwelling-places, O Lord of hosts!
019	PSA	084	002	My soul desired, yea, it also longed for the courts of the Lord: my heart and my flesh shout with joy unto the living God.
019	PSA	084	003	Even as the sparrow hath found a house, and the swallow a nest for herself, where she may lay her young: —[have I found] thy altars, O Lord of hosts, my King, and my God.
019	PSA	084	004	Happy are they who dwell in thy house: they will be continually praising thee. (Selah)
019	PSA	084	005	Happy is the man whose strong confidence is in thee, [all] whose heart reflecteth on the paths [of righteousness].
019	PSA	084	006	Passing through the valley of weeping, they will change it into a spring: also the early rain covereth it with blessings.
019	PSA	084	007	They go from strength to strength, each of them appeareth before God in Zion.
019	PSA	084	008	O Lord God of hosts, hear my prayer: give ear, O God of Jacob. (Selah)
019	PSA	084	009	[Thou,] our shield, behold, O God, and look upon the face of thy anointed.
019	PSA	084	010	For better is a day in thy courts than a thousand [elsewhere]: I would rather choose to wait at the threshold of the house of my God, than to dwell in the tents of wickedness.
019	PSA	084	011	For a sun and shield is the Lord God; grace and glory will the Lord give; he will not withhold any good from those that walk with integrity.
019	PSA	084	012	O Lord of hosts, happy is the man that trusteth in thee.
019	PSA	085	001	“To the chief musician, by the sons of Korach, a psalm.” Thou hast been favorable, O Lord, unto thy land: thou hast brought back the captivity of Jacob.
019	PSA	085	002	Thou hast forgiven the iniquity of thy people: thou hast covered over all their sin. (Selah)
019	PSA	085	003	Thou hast taken away all thy wrath: thou hast relinquished the fierceness of thy anger.
019	PSA	085	004	Return to us, O God of our salvation, and cause thy ill-will toward us to cease.
019	PSA	085	005	Wilt thou be wroth with us for ever? wilt thou extend thy anger from generation to generation?
019	PSA	085	006	Wilt thou not [now] revive us again, that thy people may rejoice in thee?
019	PSA	085	007	Show us thy kindness, O Lord, and grant us thy salvation.
019	PSA	085	008	I will hear what God the Lord will speak; for he will speak peace unto his people, and to his pious ones: only let them not turn again to folly.
019	PSA	085	009	Surely, nigh is his salvation unto those that fear him: that glory may dwell in our land.
019	PSA	085	010	Kindness and truth are met together: righteousness and peace kiss each other.
019	PSA	085	011	Truth will grow up out of the earth, and righteousness will look down from heaven.
019	PSA	085	012	Yea, the Lord will also give the good, and our land will yield its products.
019	PSA	085	013	Righteousness will walk firmly before him, and will make [level] the way by its steps.
019	PSA	086	001	“A prayer of David.” Incline, O Lord, thy ear, answer me; for poor and needy am I.
019	PSA	086	002	Preserve my soul; for I am pious: help thy servant, O thou my God, that trusteth in thee.
019	PSA	086	003	Be gracious unto me, O Lord; for unto thee I call all the time.
019	PSA	086	004	Cause to rejoice the soul of thy servant; for unto thee, O Lord, do I lift my soul.
019	PSA	086	005	For thou, O Lord, art good and forgiving, and abundant in kindness unto all that call on thee.
019	PSA	086	006	Give ear, O Lord, unto my prayer, and attend to the voice of my supplications.
019	PSA	086	007	On the day of my distress will I call on thee; for thou wilt answer me.
019	PSA	086	008	There is none like unto thee among the Gods, O Lord; and there is nothing like thy works.
019	PSA	086	009	All the nations whom thou hast made shall come and bow themselves down before thee, O Lord; and they shall ascribe honor unto thy name.
019	PSA	086	010	For great art thou, and doing wondrous things: thou art God by thyself alone.
019	PSA	086	011	Teach me, O Lord, thy way; I will walk firmly in thy truth: unite my heart to fear thy name.
019	PSA	086	012	I will thank thee, O Lord my God, with all my heart, and I will honor thy name for evermore.
019	PSA	086	013	For thy kindness is great toward me: and thou hast delivered my soul from the grave of the lower world.
019	PSA	086	014	O God, the presumptuous are risen up against me, and the assembly of the powerful wicked have sought after my life, and have not set thee before them.
019	PSA	086	015	But thou, O Lord, art God, full of mercy, and gracious, longsuffering, and abundant in kindness and truth.
019	PSA	086	016	Oh turn unto me, and be gracious unto me: give thy strength unto thy servant, and save the son of thy handmaid.
019	PSA	086	017	Display on me a sign for good, that those who hate me may see it, and be ashamed; because thou, Lord, hast helped me, and comforted me.
019	PSA	087	001	“By the sons of Korach; a psalm or song.” It is founded by him on holy mountains.
019	PSA	087	002	The Lord loveth the gates of Zion more than all the dwellings of Jacob.
019	PSA	087	003	Glorious things are spoken of thee, O city of God. (Selah)
019	PSA	087	004	I will make mention of Rahab and Babylon as those that know me; behold, here is Philistia, and Tyre, with Ethiopia: “This man was born there.”
019	PSA	087	005	But of Zion will it be said, “This and that man were born in her:” and the Most High himself doth establish her.
