019	PSA	090	001	BOOK FOURTH: “A prayer of Moses the man of God.” Lord, a place of refuge hast thou been unto us in all generations.
019	PSA	090	002	Before yet the mountains were brought forth, or thou hadst ever produced the earth and the world, even from everlasting to everlasting, thou art God.
019	PSA	090	003	Thou turnest man to contrition, and sayest, Return ye children of men.
019	PSA	090	004	For a thousand years are in thy eyes but as the yesterday when it is past, and as a watch in the night.
019	PSA	090	005	Thou carriest them away as with a flood; they are as a sleep: in the morning [they grow] like the grass which changeth.
019	PSA	090	006	In the morning it blossometh, and is changed: in the evening it is mowed off, and withereth.
019	PSA	090	007	For [thus] are we consumed by thy anger, and by thy fury are we terrified.
019	PSA	090	008	Thou hast set our iniquities before thee, our concealed sins before the light of thy countenance.
