019	PSA	090	010	The days of our years in this life are seventy years; and if by uncommon vigor they be eighty, yet is their greatness trouble and mishap; for it soon hasteneth off, and we fly away.
019	PSA	090	011	Who knoweth the strength of thy anger, and thy wrath which is like the fear of thee?
