019	PSA	090	013	Return, O Lord, how long yet? and bethink thee concerning thy servants.
019	PSA	090	014	O satisfy us in the morning with thy kindness, that we may be glad and rejoice throughout all our days.
019	PSA	090	015	Cause us to rejoice as many days as those wherein thou hast afflicted us, the years wherein we have seen unhappiness.
019	PSA	090	016	Let thy act be visible on thy servants, and thy majesty over their children.
019	PSA	090	017	And may the beauty of the Lord our God be upon us; and the work of our hands do thou firmly establish upon us: yea, the work of our hands—firmly establish thou it.
019	PSA	091	001	He who sitteth under the secret protection of the Most High, shall rest under the shadow of the Almighty.
019	PSA	091	002	I will say of the Lord, who is my refuge and my stronghold, my God, in whom I ever trust,
019	PSA	091	003	That he will surely deliver thee from the snare of the fowler, and from the pestilence of destruction.
019	PSA	091	004	With his pinions will he cover thee, and under his wings shalt thou find shelter: shield and buckler is his truth.
019	PSA	091	005	Thou shalt not be afraid of the terror of the night; nor of the arrow that flieth by day;
019	PSA	091	006	Nor of the pestilence that stalketh in darkness; nor of the deadly disease that wasteth at noonday.
019	PSA	091	007	There shall fall at thy side a thousand, and ten thousand at thy right hand; unto thee [however] shall it not come nigh.
019	PSA	091	008	Only with thy eyes shalt thou behold it, and see the recompense of the wicked.
019	PSA	091	009	Because thou hast [said], The Lord is my protection, the Most High hast thou made thy refuge:
019	PSA	091	010	No evil shall befall thee, nor shall any plague come nigh unto thy tent.
019	PSA	091	011	For his angels will he give charge concerning thee, to guard thee on all thy ways.
019	PSA	091	012	Upon [their] hands shall they bear thee, that thou mayest not dash against a stone thy foot.
019	PSA	091	013	Upon the fierce lion and asp shalt thou tread: thou shalt trample under foot the young lion and serpent.
