019	PSA	119	160	The summit of thy word is truth: and the whole of thy righteous judgment endureth for ever.
019	PSA	119	161	SHIN. Princes have persecuted me without a cause; but of thy word standeth my heart in dread.
019	PSA	119	162	I am rejoiced over thy promise, as one that findeth great spoil.
019	PSA	119	163	Falsehood I hate and abhor: but thy law do I love.
019	PSA	119	164	Seven times in the day do I praise thee because of thy righteous decrees.
019	PSA	119	165	Abundant peace have they who love thy law; and thee is nothing that causeth them to stumble.
019	PSA	119	166	I have hoped for thy salvation, O Lord, and thy commandments have I fulfilled.
019	PSA	119	167	My soul hath observed thy testimonies, and I love them exceedingly.
019	PSA	119	168	I have observed thy precepts and thy testimonies; because all my ways are before thee.
019	PSA	119	169	TAV. Let my entreaty come near before thee, O Lord: according to thy word grant me understanding.
019	PSA	119	170	Let my supplication come before thee: according to thy promise do thou deliver me.
019	PSA	119	171	My lips shall utter praise; because thou wilt teach me thy statutes.
019	PSA	119	172	My tongue shall speak loudly of thy promise; for all thy commandments are righteous.
019	PSA	119	173	Let thy hand be [ready] to help me; for thy precepts have I chosen.
019	PSA	119	174	I have longed for thy salvation, O Lord; and thy law is my delights.
019	PSA	119	175	Let my soul live, and it shall praise thee: and let thy decrees help me.
019	PSA	119	176	I have gone erringly astray like a lost sheep: seek thy servant; for thy commandments have I not forgotten.
019	PSA	120	001	“A song of the degrees.” Unto the Lord, when I was in distress, did I call, and he hath answered me.
019	PSA	120	002	O Lord, deliver my soul from lips of falsehood, and from a tongue of deceit.
019	PSA	120	003	What will [God] give unto thee? or what will he add unto thee, thou tongue of deceit?
019	PSA	120	004	Sharpened arrows of the mighty, with coals of the broom-bush.
019	PSA	120	005	Woe is me, that I sojourn in Meshech, that I dwell in the tents of Kedar!
019	PSA	120	006	Too long for herself hath my soul dwelt with him that hateth peace.
019	PSA	120	007	I am for peace; but when I speak, they are for war.
019	PSA	121	001	“A song for the degrees.” I lift up my eyes unto the mountains: whence shall come my help?
019	PSA	121	002	My help is from the Lord, the maker of heaven and earth.
019	PSA	121	003	He will not suffer thy foot to slip: thy keeper doth not slumber.
019	PSA	121	004	Behold, he slumbereth not, and he sleepeth not—the keeper of Israel.
019	PSA	121	005	The Lord is thy keeper: the Lord is thy shade, he is on thy right hand.
019	PSA	121	006	By day the sun shall not strike thee, nor the moon by night.
019	PSA	121	007	The Lord will guard thee against all evil: he will guard thy soul.
019	PSA	121	008	The Lord will guard thy going out and thy coming in from this time forth and for evermore.
019	PSA	122	001	“A song of the degrees by David.” I was rejoiced when they said unto me, Unto the house of the Lord let us go.
019	PSA	122	002	Our feet are now standing within thy gates, O Jerusalem!
019	PSA	122	003	Jerusalem, which art built as a city wherein all associate together.
019	PSA	122	004	For thither go up the tribes of the Lord, as a testimony for Israel, to give thanks unto the name of the Lord.
019	PSA	122	005	For there are placed chairs for [giving] judgment, the chairs for the house of David.—
019	PSA	122	006	Pray ye for the peace of Jerusalem; may those that love thee prosper.
019	PSA	122	007	May there be peace within thy walls, prosperity within thy palaces,
019	PSA	122	008	For the sake of my brethren and my friends, let me now speak, Peace be within thee.
019	PSA	122	009	For the sake of the house of the Lord our God, will I seek thy good.
019	PSA	123	001	“A song of the degrees.” Unto thee do I lift up my eyes, O thou that dwellest in the heavens.
019	PSA	123	002	Behold, as the eyes of servants are directed unto the hand of their masters, as the eyes of a maiden unto the hand of her mistress: thus are our eyes directed unto the Lord our God, until he be gracious unto us.
019	PSA	123	003	Be gracious unto us, O Lord! be gracious unto us; for we are overburdened with contempt.
019	PSA	123	004	Our soul is overburdened with the scorn of those who are at ease, with the contempt of the proud oppressors.
019	PSA	124	001	“A song of the degrees by David.” If it had not been the Lord who was for us, so should Israel say;
019	PSA	124	002	If it had not been the Lord who was for us, when men rose up against us:
019	PSA	124	003	Then would they have swallowed us up alive, when their wrath was kindled against us;
019	PSA	124	004	Then would the waters have overwhelmed us, the stream would have passed over our soul;
019	PSA	124	005	Then would have passed over our soul the presumptuous waters.
019	PSA	124	006	Blessed be the Lord, who hath not given us up as a prey to their teeth.
019	PSA	124	007	Our soul is escaped like a bird out of the snare of the fowlers: the snare is broken, and we are escaped.
019	PSA	124	008	Our help is in the name of the Lord, the maker of heaven and earth.
019	PSA	125	001	“A song of the degrees.” Those who trust in the Lord are like mount Zion, which will not he moved, which endureth for ever.
019	PSA	125	002	Jerusalem hath mountains round about her: and [so] is the Lord round about his people, from this time forth and for evermore.
019	PSA	125	003	For the sceptre of wickedness shall not rest upon the lot of the righteous: in order that the righteous may not stretch forth their hands unto wrong-doing.
019	PSA	125	004	Do good, O Lord, unto the good, and to those that are upright in their hearts.
019	PSA	125	005	But as for those who turn aside unto their crooked ways, them will the Lord drive away with the workers of wickedness; but peace shall be upon Israel.
019	PSA	126	001	“A song of the degrees.” When the Lord bringeth back again the captivity of Zion, then shall we be like dreamers.
019	PSA	126	002	Then shall our mouth be filled with laughter, and our tongue with singing: then shall they say among the nations, Great things hath the Lord done for these.
019	PSA	126	003	Great things would the Lord have done for us, [whereat] we should be joyful.
019	PSA	126	004	Bring back again, O Lord, our captivity, like rivulets in arid land.
019	PSA	126	005	Those that sow in tears shall reap with joyful song.
019	PSA	126	006	He goeth forth indeed and weepeth, that beareth the seed for sowing; but he will surely come with joyful song when he beareth [home] his sheaves.
019	PSA	127	001	“A song of the degrees for Solomon.” Unless the Lord do build the house, in vain labor they that build on it: unless the Lord guard the city, in vain is the watchman wakeful.
019	PSA	127	002	It is in vain for you to be early in rising, to be late in sitting up, eating the bread of painful toils; [for] so doth he give unto his beloved during sleep.
019	PSA	127	003	Lo, children are an inheritance from the Lord: a reward is the fruit of the body.
019	PSA	127	004	Like arrows in the hand of a mighty man, so are the children of youth.
019	PSA	127	005	Happy is the man that hath his quiver filled with them: they shall not be put to shame, when they do speak with the enemies in the gate.
019	PSA	128	001	“A song of the degrees.” Happy is every one that feareth the Lord, that walketh in his ways.
019	PSA	128	002	When thou eatest the labor of thy hands: [then] wilt thou be happy, and it shall be well with thee.
019	PSA	128	003	Thy wife is [then] as a fruitful vine in the recesses of thy house: thy children, like olive-plants round about thy table.
019	PSA	128	004	Behold, truly thus shall be blessed the man that feareth the Lord.
019	PSA	128	005	May the Lord bless thee out of Zion: and see thou the happiness of Jerusalem all the days of thy life.
019	PSA	128	006	And see thou thy children's children: may there be peace upon Israel.
019	PSA	129	001	“A song of the degrees.” Many a time have they assailed me from my youth, so should Israel say;
019	PSA	129	002	Many a time have they assailed me from my youth: yet have they not prevailed against me.
019	PSA	129	003	Upon my back have ploughmen ploughed; they have drawn long their furrows:
019	PSA	129	004	[Yet] the Lord is righteous; he hath cut asunder the cords of the wicked.
019	PSA	129	005	May all be put to shame and turned backward that hate Zion;
019	PSA	129	006	May they become like the grass of the roofs, which withereth before it is pulled up;
019	PSA	129	007	Wherewith the mower filleth not his hand; nor his arm he that bindeth sheaves.
019	PSA	129	008	Nor do they who pass by say, The blessing of the Lord be with you: we bless you in the name of the Lord.
019	PSA	130	001	“A song of the degrees.” Out of the depths have I called thee, O Lord.
019	PSA	130	002	Lord, listen to my voice: let thy ears be attentive to the voice of my supplications.
019	PSA	130	003	If thou, Lord, shouldst treasure up iniquities, O Lord, who would be able to stand?
019	PSA	130	004	But with thee there is forgiveness, in order that thou mayest be feared.
019	PSA	130	005	I hope for the Lord, my soul doth hope, and for his word do I wait.
019	PSA	130	006	My soul [waiteth] for the Lord, more than they that watch for the morning expect the morning.
019	PSA	130	007	Let Israel wait for the Lord; for with the Lord there is kindness, and with him is redemption in abundance;
019	PSA	130	008	And he wilt surely redeem Israel from all his iniquities.
019	PSA	131	001	“A song of the degrees by David.” O Lord, my heart was not haughty, nor were my eyes lofty: neither have I walked after matters too great, or those too wonderful for me.
019	PSA	131	002	Surely I have pacified and stilled my soul, like the suckling on its mother's breast: like a suckling is in me my soul.
019	PSA	131	003	Let Israel wait for the Lord from this time forth and for ever more.
019	PSA	132	001	“A song of the degrees.” Remember, O Lord, unto David all his afflictions;
019	PSA	132	002	How he swore unto the Lord; how he vowed unto the mighty One of Jacob:
019	PSA	132	003	Surely, I will not enter into the tent of my house, nor ascend the couch of my repose;
019	PSA	132	004	I will not grant any sleep to my eyes, nor to my eyelids any slumber:
019	PSA	132	005	Until I shall have found out a place for the Lord, a dwelling-place for the mighty One of Jacob.
019	PSA	132	006	“Lo, we heard of it at Ephratah: we met with it in the fields of the forest:
019	PSA	132	007	let us then go into his dwelling: let us prostrate ourselves before his footstool.”
019	PSA	132	008	Arise, O Lord, unto thy resting-place: thou, and the ark of thy strength.
019	PSA	132	009	Let thy priests be clothed with righteousness; and let thy pious servants shout for joy.
019	PSA	132	010	For the sake of David thy servant turn not away the face of thy anointed.
019	PSA	132	011	The Lord hath sworn unto David in truth; he will not turn from it: “From the fruit of thy body will I set [some one] on the throne to succeed thee.
019	PSA	132	012	If thy children will observe my covenant and this my testimony which I teach them: then also shall their children sit for evermore upon the throne to succeed thee.”
019	PSA	132	013	For the Lord hath made choice of Zion: he hath desired it as a habitation for himself.
019	PSA	132	014	This is my resting-place for evermore: here will I dwell; for I have desired it.
019	PSA	132	015	Her provision will I bless abundantly: her needy ones will I satisfy with bread.
019	PSA	132	016	And her priests will I clothe with salvation: and her pious ones shall shout aloud for joy.
019	PSA	132	017	There will I cause to grow a horn unto David: I arrange a lamp for my anointed.
019	PSA	132	018	His enemies will I clothe with shame; but upon himself shall his crown shine brilliantly.
019	PSA	133	001	“A song of the degrees by David.” Behold, how good and how pleasant it is! when brethren dwell closely together [in union]!
019	PSA	133	002	[It is] like the precious oil upon the head, running down upon the beard, yea, Aaron's beard, which runneth down upon the upper border of his garments;
019	PSA	133	003	Like the dew of Chermon, running down upon the mountains of Zion; for there hath the Lord commanded the blessing, even life for evermore.
019	PSA	134	001	“A song of the degrees.” Arise! bless ye the Lord, all ye servants of the Lord that stand in the house of the Lord in the nights.
019	PSA	134	002	Lift up your hands toward the sanctuary, and bless the Lord.
019	PSA	134	003	May the Lord bless thee out of Zion, he that is the maker of heaven and earth.
019	PSA	135	001	Hallelujah. Praise ye the name of the Lord; praise him, O ye servants of the Lord;
019	PSA	135	002	Ye that stand in the house of the Lord, in the courts of the house of our God.
019	PSA	135	003	Hallelujah; for the Lord is good: sing praises unto his name; for it is lovely.
019	PSA	135	004	For Jacob hath the Lord chosen unto himself, Israel, as his peculiar treasure.
019	PSA	135	005	For I well know that the Lord is great, and that our Lord is above all gods.
019	PSA	135	006	Whatsoever the Lord willeth, hath he done in the heavens, and on the earth, in the seas, and in all the deeps.
019	PSA	135	007	He causeth clouds to ascend from the ends of the earth; he maketh lightnings with the rain; he bringeth forth the wind out of his treasuries.
019	PSA	135	008	[He it is] who smote the first-born of Egypt, both of man and of cattle;
019	PSA	135	009	Who sent signs and wonderful tokens into the midst of thee, O Egypt, against Pharaoh, and against all his servants;
019	PSA	135	010	Who smote many nations, and slew mighty kings;
019	PSA	135	011	Sichon the king of the Emorites, and 'Og the king of Bashan, and all the kingdoms of Canaan;
019	PSA	135	012	And gave their land as an inheritance, an inheritance unto Israel his people.
019	PSA	135	013	O Lord, thy name [endureth] for ever: O Lord, thy memorial is throughout all generations.
019	PSA	135	014	For the Lord will espouse the cause of his people, and concerning his servants will he bethink himself.
019	PSA	135	015	The idols of the nations are silver and gold, the work of the hands of men.
019	PSA	135	016	Mouths they have, but they speak not; eyes they have, but they see not;
019	PSA	135	017	Ears they have, but they hear not; neither is there any breath in their mouth.
019	PSA	135	018	Like them are those that make them, every one that trusteth in them.
019	PSA	135	019	O house of Israel, bless ye the Lord; O house of Aaron, bless ye the Lord.
019	PSA	135	020	O house of Levi, bless ye the Lord; ye that fear the Lord, bless the Lord.
019	PSA	135	021	Blessed be the Lord out of Zion, even he that resideth at Jerusalem. Hallelujah.
019	PSA	136	001	O give thanks unto the Lord; for he is good; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	002	O give thanks unto the God of gods; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	003	O give thanks to the Lord of lords; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	004	To him who doth great wonders alone; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	005	To him that made the heavens with understanding; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	006	To him that stretched out the earth above the waters; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	007	To him that made great lights; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	008	The sun for the rule by day; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	009	The moon and stars for the rule by night; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	010	To him that smote Egypt in their first-born; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	011	And brought out Israel from the midst of them; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	012	With a strong hand, and with an outstretched arm; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	013	To him who divided the Red Sea into parts; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	014	And caused Israel to pass through the midst of it; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	015	But overthrew Pharaoh and his host in the Red Sea; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	016	To him who led his people through the wilderness; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	017	To him who smote great kings; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	018	And slew mighty kings; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	019	Even Sichon the king of the Emorites; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	020	And 'Og the king of Bashan; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	021	And gave their land as an inheritance; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	022	As an inheritance unto Israel his servant; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	023	Who hath in our low estate remembered us; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	024	And hath freed us from our assailants; for to eternity endureth his kindness;
019	PSA	136	025	Who giveth food unto all flesh; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	136	026	O give thanks unto the God of the heavens; for to eternity endureth his kindness.
019	PSA	137	001	By the rivers of Babylon, there we sat, and we also wept when we remembered Zion.
019	PSA	137	002	Upon the willows in her midst had we hung up our harps.
019	PSA	137	003	For there our captors demanded of us the words of song; and those that mocked us, joy, [saying,] Sing for us one of the songs of Zion.
019	PSA	137	004	How should we sing the song of the Lord on the soil of the stranger?
019	PSA	137	005	If I forget thee, O Jerusalem, may my right hand forget—.
019	PSA	137	006	May my tongue cleave to my palate if I do not remember thee: if I recall not Jerusalem at the head of my joy.
019	PSA	137	007	Remember, O Lord, unto the children of Edom the day of Jerusalem; who said, Raze it, raze it, even to her very foundation.
019	PSA	137	008	O daughter of Babylon, who art wasted: happy he, that repayeth thee thy recompense for what thou hast done to us.
019	PSA	137	009	Happy he, that seizeth and dasheth thy babes against the rock.
019	PSA	138	001	“By David.” I will praise thee with my whole heart: before [thee], O God, will I sing praise unto thee.
019	PSA	138	002	I will bow myself down before thy holy temple, and I will thank thy name for thy kindness and for thy truth; for thou hast magnified above all thy name thy promise.
019	PSA	138	003	On the day when I called didst thou answer me, and raise me up with strength in my soul.
019	PSA	138	004	All the kings of the earth will give thanks unto thee, O Lord, when they hear the promises of thy mouth.
019	PSA	138	005	And they will sing on the ways of the Lord; for great is the glory of the Lord.
019	PSA	138	006	For exalted is the Lord, yet doth he regard the lowly; but the proud he punisheth from afar.
019	PSA	138	007	If I should walk in the midst of distress, thou wilt revive me: against the wrath of my enemies wilt thou stretch forth thy hand, and thy right hand will save me.
019	PSA	138	008	The Lord will accomplish [all] in my behalf; O Lord, thy kindness endureth for ever: the works of thy own hands do not abandon.
019	PSA	139	001	“To the chief musician, by David, a psalm.” O Lord! thou hast searched me through, and thou knowest [me].
019	PSA	139	002	Thou indeed knowest my sitting down and my rising up, thou understandest my thinking while yet afar off.
019	PSA	139	003	My walking and my lying down hast thou limited, and with all my ways art thou acquainted.
019	PSA	139	004	For, while there is not a word on my tongue, lo, thou, O Lord, knowest it entirely.
019	PSA	139	005	Behind and before hast thou hedged me in, and thou placest upon me thy hand.
019	PSA	139	006	Too wonderful is such knowledge for me: it is too exalted, I cannot attain unto it.
019	PSA	139	007	Whither shall I go from thy spirit? or whither shall I flee away from thy presence?
019	PSA	139	008	If I should ascend into heaven, thou art there; and if I should make my bed in the nether world, behold, thou art there.
019	PSA	139	009	If I should lift up the wings of the morning-dawn, if I should dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea:
019	PSA	139	010	Even there would thy hand lead me, and thy right hand would seize hold of me.
019	PSA	139	011	If I said, Surely darkness shall enshroud me, and into night [be turned] the light about me:
019	PSA	139	012	Yet even darkness can obscure nothing from thee; but the night will shine like the day; both the darkness and the light are alike [to thee].
019	PSA	139	013	For thou possessest my reins: thou hast covered me in my mother's womb.
019	PSA	139	014	I will thank thee therefore, that I am [so] fearfully [and] wonderfully made: wonderful are thy works; and that my soul knoweth right well.
019	PSA	139	015	My being was not concealed from thee, when I was made in secret, when I was [so to say] embroidered in the lowest parts of the earth.
019	PSA	139	016	My undeveloped substance did thy eyes see; and in thy book were all of them written down—the days which have been formed, while yet not one of them was here.
019	PSA	139	017	And how precious are unto me thy thoughts, O God! how mightily great is their sum!
019	PSA	139	018	Should I count them, they would be more numerous than the sand: I awake, and I am still with thee.
019	PSA	139	019	If thou wouldst but slay the wicked, O God! and ye men of blood, depart from me.
019	PSA	139	020	Who speak of thee for a wicked end, thy enemies, that bear [thy name] for a vain purpose.
019	PSA	139	021	Behold, those that hate thee I ever hate, O Lord; and for those that rise up against thee do I feel loathing.
019	PSA	139	022	With the utmost hatred do I hate them: enemies are they become unto me.
019	PSA	139	023	Search me through, O God, and know my heart; probe me, and know my thoughts:
019	PSA	139	024	And see if there be a way of perverseness in me, and lead me on the way of eternity.
019	PSA	140	001	“To the chief musician, a psalm of David.” Deliver me, O Lord, from an evil man; from a man of violence do thou keep me;
019	PSA	140	002	Who think over evil [resolves] in their heart, [who] every day are gathered together for war.
019	PSA	140	003	They have sharpened their tongues like a serpent: the poison of the adder is under their lips. (Selah)
019	PSA	140	004	Preserve me, O Lord, from the hands of the wicked, from the man of violence do thou keep me, who think of overthrowing my steps.
019	PSA	140	005	The proud have hidden a snare for me, and cords; they have spread a net by the side of [my] track; traps have they set for me. (Selah)
019	PSA	140	006	I have said unto the Lord, Thou art my God: give ear, O Lord, to the voice of my supplications.
019	PSA	140	007	O thou Eternal Lord, the strength of my salvation, thou hast covered my head on the day of battle.
019	PSA	140	008	Grant not, O Lord, the longings of the wicked; suffer not his wicked device to succeed: lest they exalt themselves. (Selah)
019	PSA	140	009	[As for] the heads of those that encompass me about, let the mischief of their own lips cover them.
019	PSA	140	010	Let burning coals be cast upon them: let them be thrown into the fire; into deep pits, that they rise not up again.
019	PSA	140	011	Let not the man of an [evil] tongue be established on the earth: may evil hunt down the violent man to his downfall.
019	PSA	140	012	I know that the Lord will procure right for the afflicted, [and] justice for the needy.
019	PSA	140	013	Surely the righteous shall give thanks unto thy name: the upright shall dwell before thy presence.
019	PSA	141	001	“A psalm of David.” O Lord, I call thee, hasten unto me: give ear unto my voice, when I call unto thee.
019	PSA	141	002	May my prayer be valued as incense before thee, the lifting up of my hands, as the evening offering.
019	PSA	141	003	Set, O Lord, a watch unto my mouth: keep a guard at the door of my lips.
019	PSA	141	004	Permit not my heart to incline after any evil thing, to practise deeds in wickedness with men that are doers of wrong: and let me not eat of their dainties.
019	PSA	141	005	If the righteous strike me, it is a kindness; and if he reprove me, it is [as] oil poured on the head, my head shall not refuse it; for yet my prayer also [is offered] in their sufferings.
019	PSA	141	006	Are their judges fallen down through means of a rock: then will they listen to my words; for they are pleasant.
019	PSA	141	007	As when one cutteth in and splitteth open the earth: so are our bones scattered for the mouth of the grave.
019	PSA	141	008	For unto thee, O Eternal Lord, are my eyes directed; in thee do I trust: pour not out my life.
019	PSA	141	009	Guard me from the power of the snare which they have laid for me, and the traps of the wrong-doers.
019	PSA	141	010	Let the wicked fall into their own nets, altogether—while I pass safely by.
019	PSA	142	001	“A Maskil of David, when he was in the cave. A prayer.” With my voice I cry unto the Lord: with my voice I make supplication unto the Lord.
019	PSA	142	002	I pour out before him my grief: my distress I recite before him.
019	PSA	142	003	When my spirit was overwhelmed within me—and thou knowest well my path—on the way whereon I desired to walk they had secretly laid a snare for me.
019	PSA	142	004	Look to the right, and behold, yea, there is no man that recognizeth me: [every] refuge is lost to me; there is no one that careth for my soul.
019	PSA	142	005	I cried unto thee, O Lord: I said, Thou art my refuge, my portion in the land of life.
019	PSA	142	006	Listen unto my entreaty; for I am very miserable: deliver me from my pursuers; for they are too mighty for me.
019	PSA	142	007	Bring forth out of prison my soul, that I may thank thy name: with me shall the righteous crown themselves, when thou wilt deal bountifully with me.
019	PSA	143	001	“A psalm of David.” O Lord, hear my prayer, give ear to my supplications: in thy faithfulness answer me, in thy righteousness.
019	PSA	143	002	And enter not into judgment with thy servant; for no living man can be regarded righteous before thee.
019	PSA	143	003	For the enemy hath pursued my soul; he hath crushed to the ground my life; he hath made me dwell in darkness, as those that are dead eternally.
019	PSA	143	004	And my spirit within me is overwhelmed: in my bosom is my heart astounded.
019	PSA	143	005	I remember the days of olden times: I meditate on all thy doings: on the work of thy hands do I reflect.
019	PSA	143	006	I spread forth my hands unto thee: my soul [longeth] for thee, as a thirsty land. (Selah)
019	PSA	143	007	Hasten, answer me, O Lord, my spirit falleth: hide not thy face from me, that I may not become like those that go down into the pit.
019	PSA	143	008	Cause me to hear in the morning thy kindness; for in thee do I trust: cause me to know the way whereon I should walk; for unto thee do I lift up my soul.
019	PSA	143	009	Deliver me, O Lord, from my enemies: by thee do I seek shelter.
019	PSA	143	010	Teach me to do thy will; for thou art my God: thy spirit is good; guide me on a level land.
019	PSA	143	011	For thy sake, O Lord, revive me: in thy righteousness bring forth out of distress my soul.
019	PSA	143	012	And in thy kindness destroy my enemies, and annihilate all the adversaries of my soul; far I am thy servant.
019	PSA	144	001	“By David.” Blessed be the Lord my Rock, who exerciseth my hands for the battle, my fingers for the war:
019	PSA	144	002	My kindness, and my strong-hold; my high tower, and my deliverer; my shield, and he in whom I trust; who subdueth my people under me.
019	PSA	144	003	Lord, what is man, that thou takest cognizance of him: the son of a mortal, that thou regardest him!
019	PSA	144	004	Man is like the breath: his days are like a passing shadow.
019	PSA	144	005	O Lord, bend thy heavens, and come down: touch the mountains, that they may smoke.
019	PSA	144	006	Cast forth lightning, and scatter them: send out thy arrows, and confound them.
019	PSA	144	007	Stretch out thy hands from above; rid me, and deliver me out of great waters, from the hand of the children of the stranger.
019	PSA	144	008	Whose mouth speaketh vanity, and whose right hand is the right hand of falsehood.
019	PSA	144	009	O God, a new song will I sing unto thee: upon the ten-stringed psaltery will I sing praises unto thee.
019	PSA	144	010	[Thou art he] that giveth victory unto kings: who riddeth David his servant from the evil-bringing sword.
019	PSA	144	011	Rid me, and deliver me from the hand of the children of the stranger, whose mouth speaketh vanity, and whose right hand is the right hand of falsehood.
019	PSA	144	012	So that our sons may be like plants, grown up in their youth: our daughters, like corner-pillars, sculptured in the model of a palace.
019	PSA	144	013	May our garners be full, furnishing all manner of store: our sheep bringing forth thousands and ten thousands in our open pastures.
019	PSA	144	014	May our oxen be strong to labor: may there be no breach, nor migration, nor loud complaint in our streets.
019	PSA	144	015	Happy the people, that fare thus: happy the people, whose God is the Lord.
019	PSA	145	001	“A hymn of praise by David.” I will extol thee, my God, O king; and I will bless thy name for ever and ever.
019	PSA	145	002	Every day will I bless thee, and I will praise thy name for ever and ever.
019	PSA	145	003	Great is the Lord, and greatly praised, and his greatness is unsearchable.
019	PSA	145	004	One generation shall praise thy works to the other, and thy mighty acts shall they declare.
019	PSA	145	005	On the majestic glory of thy excellence, and on thy wondrous deeds will I meditate.
019	PSA	145	006	And of the might of thy terrible acts shall men converse: and thy greatness will I relate.
019	PSA	145	007	The memorial of thy abundant goodness shall they loudly proclaim, and they shall sing joyfully of thy righteousness.
019	PSA	145	008	Gracious and merciful is the Lord, long-suffering, and great in kindness.
019	PSA	145	009	The Lord is good to all, and his mercies are over all his works.
019	PSA	145	010	All thy works shall thank thee, O Lord; and thy pious servants shall bless thee.
019	PSA	145	011	Of the glory of thy kingdom shall they converse, and of thy might shall they speak:
019	PSA	145	012	To make known to the sons of men his mighty acts, and the glorious majesty of his kingdom.
019	PSA	145	013	Thy kingdom is a kingdom of all eternities, and thy dominion [subsisteth] throughout all generations.
019	PSA	145	014	The Lord upholdeth all who are falling, and raiseth up all those who are bowed down.
019	PSA	145	015	The eyes of all wait hopefully upon thee, and thou givest them their food in its due season.
019	PSA	145	016	Thou openest thy hand, and satisfiest the desire of every living thing.
019	PSA	145	017	Righteous is the Lord in all his ways, and beneficent in all his works.
019	PSA	145	018	The Lord is nigh unto all those who call on him, to all who call on him in truth.
019	PSA	145	019	The desire of those who fear him will he fulfill, and their cry will he hear, and save them.
019	PSA	145	020	The Lord preserveth all those who love him; but all the wicked will he destroy.
019	PSA	145	021	The praise of the Lord shall my mouth speak: and let all flesh bless his holy name for ever and ever.
019	PSA	146	001	Hallelujah. Praise, O my soul, the Lord.
019	PSA	146	002	I will praise the Lord throughout my life: I will sing praises unto my God while I have any being.
019	PSA	146	003	Put not your trust in princes, in the son of man, in whom there is no salvation.
019	PSA	146	004	When his spirit goeth forth, he returneth to his [native] earth: on that very day perish his thoughts.
019	PSA	146	005	[But] happy is he who hath the God of Jacob for his help, whose hope is on the Lord his God;
019	PSA	146	006	Who hath made heaven, and earth, the sea, and all that is therein; who keepeth truth for ever;
019	PSA	146	007	Who executeth justice for the oppressed: who giveth bread to the hungry: the Lord looseneth the prisoners;
019	PSA	146	008	The Lord causeth the blind to see; the Lord raiseth up those who are bowed down; the Lord loveth the righteous:
019	PSA	146	009	The Lord guardeth the strangers; the fatherless and widow he helpeth up; but the way of the wicked he maketh crooked.
019	PSA	146	010	The Lord will reign for ever, even thy God, O Zion, unto all generations. Hallelujah.
019	PSA	147	001	Hallelujah; for it is good to sing praises unto our God; for it is comely; [him] becometh praise.
019	PSA	147	002	The Lord buildeth up Jerusalem: the outcasts of Israel will he gather together;
019	PSA	147	003	He that healeth the broken-hearted, and bindeth up their hurts;
019	PSA	147	004	Who counteth the number of the stars; who calleth them all by [their] names.
019	PSA	147	005	Great is our Lord, and abundant in power: his understanding is immeasurable.
019	PSA	147	006	The Lord helpeth up the meek: he bringeth down the wicked to the ground.
019	PSA	147	007	Lift up a song unto the Lord with thanksgiving; sing praises unto our God with the harp;
019	PSA	147	008	Who covereth the heaven with clouds, who prepareth rain for the earth, who causeth grass to grow upon the mountains;
019	PSA	147	009	Who giveth to the beast its food, to the young ravens which cry.
019	PSA	147	010	Not in the strength of the horse hath he delight: nor in the [swiftness of the] legs of man taketh he pleasure.
019	PSA	147	011	The Lord taketh pleasure in those that fear him, that wait for his kindness.
019	PSA	147	012	Glorify, O Jerusalem, the Lord: praise thy God, O Zion.
019	PSA	147	013	For he hath strengthened the bars of thy gates; he hath blessed thy children in the midst of thee;
019	PSA	147	014	He who bestoweth peace in thy borders, who satisfieth thee with the best of wheat;
019	PSA	147	015	He who sendeth forth his decree unto the earth: how swiftly speedeth his word along!
019	PSA	147	016	He who dispenseth snow like wool; who streweth about the hoarfrost like ashes;
019	PSA	147	017	He who casteth down his ice like pieces: before his cold who can stand?
019	PSA	147	018	He sendeth out his word, and melteth them: he causeth his wind to blow, and waters run along.
019	PSA	147	019	He declareth his word unto Jacob, his statutes and his ordinances unto Israel.
019	PSA	147	020	He hath not done so unto any nation: and [his] ordinances— these they know not. Hallelujah.
019	PSA	148	001	Hallelujah. Praise ye the Lord from the heavens: praise him in the heights.
019	PSA	148	002	Praise ye him, all his angels: praise ye him, all his hosts.
019	PSA	148	003	Praise ye him, sun and moon: praise him, all ye stars of light.
019	PSA	148	004	Praise him, ye heavens of heavens, and ye waters that are above the heavens.
019	PSA	148	005	Let them praise the name of the Lord; for he commanded and they were created.
019	PSA	148	006	And he established them for ever and to eternity: he gave a decree which none shall transgress.
019	PSA	148	007	Praise the Lord from the earth, ye sea-monsters, and all deeps;
019	PSA	148	008	Fire, and hail, snow, and vapor; thou storm-wind that fulfillest his word;
019	PSA	148	009	Ye mountains, and all hills; fruitful trees, and all cedars;
019	PSA	148	010	Ye beasts, and all cattle; creeping things, and winged birds;
019	PSA	148	011	Ye kings of the earth, and all nations; ye princes, and all judges of the earth;
019	PSA	148	012	Young men and also virgins; old men, together with boys: —
019	PSA	148	013	Let them praise the name of the Lord; for his name alone is exalted; his majesty is above earth and heaven.
019	PSA	148	014	He also exalteth the horn of his people, a praise unto all his pious servants, [even] unto the children of Israel, a people near unto him. Hallelujah.
019	PSA	149	001	Hallelujah. Sing unto the Lord a new song, his praise in the congregation of the pious.
019	PSA	149	002	Let Israel rejoice in his Maker: let the children of Zion exult in their King.
019	PSA	149	003	Let them praise his name in the dance: with the timbrel and harp let them sing praises unto him.
019	PSA	149	004	For the Lord taketh pleasure in his people; he will adorn the meek with salvation.
019	PSA	149	005	Let the pious be joyful in glory: let them sing aloud upon their couches.
019	PSA	149	006	The exalted praises of God are in their mouth, and a two-edged sword is in their hand;
019	PSA	149	007	To execute vengeance on the nations, and chastisements on the people:
019	PSA	149	008	To bind their kings with chains, and their nobles with fetters of iron:
019	PSA	149	009	To execute upon them the judgment [which is] written: this is an honor for all his pious servants. Hallelujah.
019	PSA	150	001	Hallelujah. Praise ye God in his sanctuary: praise him in the expansion of his power.
019	PSA	150	002	Praise him for his acts of might: praise him according to the abundance of his greatness.
019	PSA	150	003	Praise him with the blowing of the cornet: praise him with the psaltery and harp.
019	PSA	150	004	Praise him with the timbrel and dance: praise him with stringed instruments and pipe.
019	PSA	150	005	Praise him upon the clear-ringing cymbals: praise him upon the high-sounding cymbals.
019	PSA	150	006	Let every thing that hath breath praise the Lord. Hallelujah.
