# BOOK	020	PRO	Proverbs	Proverbs
020	PRO	001	001	The proverbs of Solomon the son of David, the king of Israel:
020	PRO	001	002	To know wisdom and instruction; to comprehend the sayings of understanding;
020	PRO	001	003	To accept the instruction of intelligence, righteousness, and justice, and equity;
020	PRO	001	004	To give to the simple prudence, to the youth knowledge and discretion.
020	PRO	001	005	The wise will hear, and will increase [his] information; and the man of understanding will obtain wise counsels:
020	PRO	001	006	To understand a proverb, and a sage sentence; the words of the wise, and their riddles.
020	PRO	001	007	The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge: wisdom and instruction fools [alone] despise.
020	PRO	001	008	Hear, my son, the instruction of thy father, and cast not off the teaching of thy mother;
020	PRO	001	009	For a wreath of grace are they unto thy head, and chains for thy throat.
020	PRO	001	010	My son, if sinners wish to entice thee, consent thou not.
020	PRO	001	011	If they should say, Come with us, let us lie in wait for blood, let us watch in concealment for the uselessly innocent;
020	PRO	001	012	We will swallow them up like the grave alive; and the men of integrity, as those that go down into the pit;
020	PRO	001	013	We shall find all [kinds of] precious wealth, we will fill our houses with booty;
020	PRO	001	014	Thy lot must thou cast in our midst; one purse shall be for us all:
020	PRO	001	015	My son, walk not thou on the way with them; withhold thy foot from their path;
020	PRO	001	016	For their feet run after evil, and they make haste to shed blood.
020	PRO	001	017	For uselessly is the net spread out before the eyes of every winged bird:
020	PRO	001	018	While they lie in wait for their [own] blood; they watch in concealment for their [own] lives.
020	PRO	001	019	So are the paths of every one that is greedy after [unlawful] gain; it taketh away the life of those that own it.
020	PRO	001	020	Wisdom crieth loudly without; in the public places she uttereth her voice;
020	PRO	001	021	At the corner of noisy streets she calleth, at the entrances of gates; in the city she sayeth her speeches:
020	PRO	001	022	How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? and the scorners take their delight in scorning, and fools hate knowledge?
020	PRO	001	023	Turn back to my admonition: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.
020	PRO	001	024	Whereas I called, and ye refused; I stretched out my hand, and no man was attentive;
020	PRO	001	025	And ye have set at nought all my counsel, and would not accept my admonition:
020	PRO	001	026	[Therefore] I also will truly laugh at your calamity; I will deride [you] when your terror cometh;
020	PRO	001	027	When your terror cometh like the tempest-cloud, and your calamity hasteneth like a whirlwind; when there come upon you distress and affliction.
020	PRO	001	028	Then will they call me, but I will not answer; they will seek me earnestly, but they shall not find me;
020	PRO	001	029	For the reason that they hated knowledge, and the fear of the Lord they did not choose;
020	PRO	001	030	[That] they would not attend to my counsel: [that] they rejected all my admonition.
020	PRO	001	031	Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and from their own counsels shall they be satisfied.
020	PRO	001	032	For the defection of the simple will slay them, and the prosperity of fools will cause them to be lost.
020	PRO	001	033	But he that hearkeneth unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be at rest from the dread of evil.
020	PRO	002	001	My son, if thou wouldst but accept my words, and treasure up my commandments with thee;
020	PRO	002	002	To let thy ear listen unto wisdom: [if] thou wouldst incline thy heart to understanding.
020	PRO	002	003	For if thou wilt call after intelligence; if after understanding thou wilt lift up thy voice;
020	PRO	002	004	If thou wilt seek her as silver, and search for her as for hidden treasures:
020	PRO	002	005	Then wilt thou understand the fear of the Lord, and the knowledge of God wilt thou find.
020	PRO	002	006	For the Lord giveth wisdom: out of his mouth [come] knowledge and understanding.
020	PRO	002	007	He treasureth up sound wisdom for the righteous, as a shield to those that walk in integrity:
020	PRO	002	008	That men may keep the paths of justice; and the way of his pious servants doth he guard.
020	PRO	002	009	Then wilt thou understand righteousness, and justice, and equity: yea, every track of goodness.
020	PRO	002	010	For wisdom will enter thy heart, and knowledge will be pleasant unto thy soul;
020	PRO	002	011	Discretion will watch over thee, understanding will keep thee;
020	PRO	002	012	To deliver thee from the way of the bad, from the man that speaketh perverse things;
020	PRO	002	013	[From those] who leave the paths of uprightness, to walk in the ways of darkness;
020	PRO	002	014	Who rejoice to do evil, who are delighted in the perverseness of the bad;
020	PRO	002	015	Who as regardeth their paths are crooked, and froward in their tracks.
020	PRO	002	016	To deliver thee from the adulteress, from the alien woman that useth flattering speeches;
020	PRO	002	017	That forsaketh the friend of her youth, and forgetteth the covenant of her God.
020	PRO	002	018	For she sinketh unto death—her house, and unto the departed [lead] her tracks.
020	PRO	002	019	All that come unto her return not again, and they will not reach the paths of life.
020	PRO	002	020	In order that thou mayest walk in the way of good men, and observe the paths of the righteous.
020	PRO	002	021	For the upright will dwell on the earth, and the perfect will be left remaining on it.
020	PRO	002	022	But the wicked will be cut off from the earth, and the treacherous shall be plucked up therefrom.
020	PRO	003	001	My son, forget not my teaching, and let thy heart keep my commandments;
020	PRO	003	002	For length of days, and years of life, and peace, will they increase unto thee.
020	PRO	003	003	Let kindness and truth not forsake thee; bind them about thy throat; write them upon the table of thy heart:
020	PRO	003	004	So shalt thou find grace and good favor in the eyes of God and man.
020	PRO	003	005	Trust in the Lord with all thy heart: and upon thy own understanding do not rely.
020	PRO	003	006	In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he will make level thy paths.
020	PRO	003	007	Be not wise in thy own eyes: fear the Lord, and depart from evil.
020	PRO	003	008	It will be healing to thy body, and marrow to thy bones.
020	PRO	003	009	Honor the Lord with thy wealth, and with the first-fruits of all thy products:
020	PRO	003	010	So shall thy storehouses be filled with plenty, and with new wine shall thy presses overflow.
020	PRO	003	011	The correction of the Lord, my son, do not despise; and feel no loathing for his admonition;
020	PRO	003	012	Because whomever the Lord loveth he admonisheth; and as a father who delighteth in [his] son.
020	PRO	003	013	Happy the man that hath found wisdom, and the man that acquireth understanding.
020	PRO	003	014	For the obtaining of her is better than the obtaining of silver, and better than fine gold is her product.
020	PRO	003	015	She is more precious than pearls; and all the things thou valuest are not equal unto her.
020	PRO	003	016	Length of days is in her right hand: in her left are riches and honor.
020	PRO	003	017	Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.
020	PRO	003	018	A tree of life is she to those that lay hold on her: and every one that firmly graspeth her will be made happy.
020	PRO	003	019	The Lord hath through wisdom founded the earth: he hath established the heavens through understanding.
020	PRO	003	020	By his knowledge were the depths split open, and the skies drop down the dew.
020	PRO	003	021	My son, let them not be removed from thy eyes; keep [before thee] sound wisdom and discretion:
020	PRO	003	022	And they will be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy throat.
020	PRO	003	023	Then wilt thou walk in safety on thy way, and thy foot will not strike [against aught]:
020	PRO	003	024	When thou layest thyself down, thou shalt feel no dread; and as thou liest down, thy sleep shall be pleasant.
020	PRO	003	025	Thou needest not to be afraid of sudden dread, neither of the [unlooked-for] tempest over the wicked, when it cometh.
020	PRO	003	026	For the Lord will be thy confidence, and he will guard thy foot from being caught.
020	PRO	003	027	Withhold not a benefit from him who is deserving it, when it is in the power of thy hand to do it.
020	PRO	003	028	Say not unto thy neighbor, Go, and return, and tomorrow will I give: when thou hast it by thee.
020	PRO	003	029	Contrive not against thy neighbor any evil, when he dwelleth in safety with thee.
020	PRO	003	030	Quarrel not with any man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.
020	PRO	003	031	Envy not the man of violence, and choose none of his ways.
020	PRO	003	032	For the froward is an abomination to the Lord; but with the upright is his good-will.
020	PRO	003	033	The curse of the Lord is in the house of the wicked; but the habitation of the righteous will he bless.
020	PRO	003	034	If [it concern] the scornful he will himself render them a scorn; but unto the lowly doth he give grace.
020	PRO	003	035	The wise shall inherit glory; but fools shall obtain disgrace as their portion.
020	PRO	004	001	Hear, ye children, the correction of a father, and attend to know understanding.
020	PRO	004	002	For good information do I give you: my teaching must ye not forsake.
020	PRO	004	003	For I was a son unto my father, a tender and an only child before my mother.
020	PRO	004	004	And he instructed me, and said unto me, Let thy heart grasp firmly my words: observe my commandments and live.
020	PRO	004	005	Acquire wisdom, acquire understanding: forget not, and depart not from the sayings of my mouth.
020	PRO	004	006	Forsake her not, and she will watch over thee: love her, and she will keep thee.
020	PRO	004	007	The beginning of wisdom is, Acquire wisdom: and with all thy acquisition acquire understanding.
020	PRO	004	008	Hold her in high esteem, and she will exalt thee: she will bring thee to honor, when thou embracest her.
020	PRO	004	009	She will give to thy head a wreath of grace: a crown of ornament will she deliver to thee.
020	PRO	004	010	Hear, O my son, and accept my sayings: and they will increase unto thee the years of life.
020	PRO	004	011	In the way of wisdom have I instructed thee: I have led thee in the tracks of uprightness.
020	PRO	004	012	When thou walkest, thy step shall not be narrowed; and when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.
020	PRO	004	013	Lay fast hold of correction; let her not go: keep her; for she is thy life.
020	PRO	004	014	Enter not into the path of the wicked, and step not on the way of the bad.
020	PRO	004	015	Avoid it, pass not through by it, turn off from it, and pass away.
020	PRO	004	016	For they sleep not, except they have done evil, and their sleep is robbed away, unless they cause some to stumble.
020	PRO	004	017	For they eat the bread of wickedness; and the wine of violence do they drink.
020	PRO	004	018	But the path of the righteous is as the early morning light, that shineth more and more brightly until the height of noonday.
020	PRO	004	019	The way of the wicked is like darkness: they know not against what they stumble.
020	PRO	004	020	My son, attend to my words, unto my sayings incline thy ear.
020	PRO	004	021	Let them not slip away from thy eyes: guard them in the midst of thy heart.
020	PRO	004	022	For they are life unto every one of those that find them, and to all his body a healing.
020	PRO	004	023	Above all that is to be guarded, keep thy heart, for out of it are the issues of life.
020	PRO	004	024	Remove from thee frowardness of mouth; and perverseness of lips put away far from thee.
020	PRO	004	025	Let thy eyes look right forward, and let thy eyelids see straight out before thee.
020	PRO	004	026	Balance well the track of thy foot, and let all thy ways be firmly right.
020	PRO	004	027	Turn not to the right hand nor to the left: remove thy foot from evil.
020	PRO	005	001	My son, attend unto my wisdom; to my understanding incline thou thy ear:
020	PRO	005	002	That thou mayest observe discretion, and that thy lips may keep knowledge.
020	PRO	005	003	For as of fine honey drop the lips of an adulterous woman, and smoother than oil is her palate;
020	PRO	005	004	But her end is bitter as wormwood, it is sharp as a two-edged sword.
020	PRO	005	005	Her feet go down to death, her steps take firm hold on the nether world:
020	PRO	005	006	So that she cannot balance the path of life; her tracks are unsteady, and she knoweth it not.
020	PRO	005	007	And now, O ye children, hearken unto me, and depart not from the sayings of my mouth.
020	PRO	005	008	Remove far from her thy way, and come not nigh to the door of her house;
020	PRO	005	009	That thou mayest not give up unto others thy vigor, and thy years unto the cruel;
020	PRO	005	010	That strangers may not satisfy themselves with thy strength, and with thy exertions, in the house of an alien:
020	PRO	005	011	While thou moanest at thy end, when thy flesh and thy body are coming to their end,
020	PRO	005	012	And thou sayest, How have I hated correction, and how hath my heart rejected reproof;
020	PRO	005	013	While I hearkened not to the voice of my instructors, and to my teachers I inclined not my ear;
020	PRO	005	014	But little more was wanting, and I had been in all [kinds of] unhappiness in the midst of the congregation and assembly.
020	PRO	005	015	Drink water out of thy own cistern, and running waters out of thy own well.
020	PRO	005	016	So will thy springs overflow abroad; and in the open streets will be thy rivulets of water;
020	PRO	005	017	They will be thy own only, and not those of strangers with thee.
020	PRO	005	018	Thy fountain will be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of thy youth, —
020	PRO	005	019	The lovely gazelle and the graceful chamois: let her bosom satisfy thee abundantly at all times; with her love be thou ravished continually.
020	PRO	005	020	And why wilt thou, my son, be ravished with an adulteress, and embrace the bosom of an alien woman?
020	PRO	005	021	For before the eyes of the Lord are the ways of man, and all his tracks doth he weigh in the balance.
020	PRO	005	022	His own iniquities will truly catch the wicked, and with the cords of his sin will he be held firmly.
020	PRO	005	023	He will indeed die for want of correction; and through the abundance of his folly will he sink into error.
020	PRO	006	001	My son, If thou hast become surety for thy friend, if thou hast struck thy hand for a stranger;
020	PRO	006	002	If thou art ensnared through the words of thy mouth, if thou art caught through the words of thy mouth:
020	PRO	006	003	[Then] do this by all means, my son, and deliver thyself, because thou art come into the power of thy friend, Go hasten to him, and urge thy friend.
020	PRO	006	004	Grant not any sleep to thy eyes, nor slumber to thy eyelids.
020	PRO	006	005	Deliver thyself as a roebuck from the hand [of the hunter], and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.
020	PRO	006	006	Go to the ant, thou sluggard; look on her ways, and become wise.
020	PRO	006	007	She, that hath no prince, officer, or ruler,
020	PRO	006	008	Provideth in the summer her provision, gathereth in harvest-time her food.
020	PRO	006	009	How long, O sluggard, wilt thou lie down? when wilt thou arise out of thy sleep?
020	PRO	006	010	“A little [more] sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands in lying down;”
020	PRO	006	011	But then will thy poverty come like a rover, and thy want as a man armed with a shield.
020	PRO	006	012	A Godless person is a man of injustice, who walketh with a distorted mouth.
020	PRO	006	013	He blinketh with his eyes, he scrapeth with his feet, he pointeth with his fingers;
020	PRO	006	014	Perverseness is in his heart, he contriveth evil at all times; he scattereth abroad discord.
020	PRO	006	015	Therefore shall suddenly come his calamity: unawares shalt he be broken without a remedy.
020	PRO	006	016	Six things there are which the Lord hateth; and seven are an abomination unto his spirit:
020	PRO	006	017	Haughty eyes, a tongue of falsehood, and hands that shed innocent blood,
020	PRO	006	018	A heart that contriveth plans of injustice, feet that hasten to run after evil,
020	PRO	006	019	A false witness that eagerly uttereth lies, and him that scattereth abroad discord among brethren.
020	PRO	006	020	Keep, O my son, the commandment of thy father, and reject not the teaching of thy mother:
020	PRO	006	021	Bind them upon thy heart continually, tie them about thy throat.
020	PRO	006	022	When thou walkest, it shall lead thee; when thou liest down, it shall watch over thee; and when thou art awake, it shall converse with thee.
020	PRO	006	023	For the commandment is a lamp, and the law is light; and the way of life are the admonitions of correction:
020	PRO	006	024	To guard thee against a bad woman, from the flattery of an alien tongue.
020	PRO	006	025	Covet not her beauty in thy heart, and let her not conquer thee with her eyelids.
020	PRO	006	026	For by means of a harlot [one is brought down] to the last loaf of bread: and an adulterous woman will even hunt for the precious life,
020	PRO	006	027	Can a man gather up fire in his lap, and shall his clothes not be burnt?
020	PRO	006	028	Can a man walk along upon hot coals, and shall his feet not be burnt?
020	PRO	006	029	So it is with him that goeth in to his neighbor's wife: no one that toucheth her shall remain unpunished.
020	PRO	006	030	Men do not despise the thief, if he steal, to gratify his craving when he is hungry:
020	PRO	006	031	And if he be found, he must pay sevenfold; all the wealth his house must he give.
020	PRO	006	032	But whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh sense: he that is the destroyer of his soul, will alone do this.
020	PRO	006	033	Plague and disgrace will he meet with; and his reproach will not be blotted out.
020	PRO	006	034	For jealousy is the fury of a husband, and he will not spare on the day of vengeance.
020	PRO	006	035	He will not regard the appearance of any ransom; and he will not be content, though thou give ever so many bribes.
020	PRO	007	001	My son, observe my sayings, and my commandments must thou treasure up with thee.
020	PRO	007	002	Observe my commandments, and live: and my teaching as the apple of thy eyes.
020	PRO	007	003	Bind them around thy fingers, write them upon the table of thy heart.
020	PRO	007	004	Say unto wisdom, Thou art my sister; and call understanding thy kinswoman:
020	PRO	007	005	That they may keep thee from an adulterous woman, from an alien that useth flattering speeches.
020	PRO	007	006	For through the window of my house, through my lattice did I [once] look out,
020	PRO	007	007	And I beheld among the simple ones, I discerned among the youths, a lad void of sense;
020	PRO	007	008	He was passing through the market-place near her corner; and he stepped along on the way to her house,
020	PRO	007	009	In the twilight, in the evening of the day, in the depth of the night and when it was dark:
020	PRO	007	010	And, behold, a woman came to meet him with the attire of a harlot, and obdurate of heart.
020	PRO	007	011	(She is noisy and ungovernable; in her house her feet never rest;
020	PRO	007	012	At one time she is in the street, at another in the open places, and near every corner doth she lurk,)
020	PRO	007	013	And she caught hold of him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face she said to him,
020	PRO	007	014	“I had bound myself to bring peace-offerings; this day have I paid my vows:
020	PRO	007	015	Therefore am I come forth to meet thee, to seek thy presence diligently, and I have found thee.
020	PRO	007	016	With tapestry coverings have I decked my bed, with embroidered coverlids of the fine linen of Egypt.
020	PRO	007	017	I have sprinkled my couch with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.
020	PRO	007	018	Come, let us indulge in love until the morning: let us delight ourselves with dalliances.
020	PRO	007	019	For the man is not in his house, he is gone on a journey a great way off:
020	PRO	007	020	The bag of money hath he taken with him, by the day of the new-moon festival only will he come home.”
020	PRO	007	021	She seduced him by the abundance of her reasoning: by the flattery of her lips she misguided him.
020	PRO	007	022	He followed after her suddenly, as an ox goeth to the slaughter, and as in fetters to his correction, the fool:
020	PRO	007	023	Till an arrow cleaveth through his liver; as a bird hasteneth into the snare, and knoweth not that it is done to take his life.
020	PRO	007	024	And now, O children, hearken unto me, and listen to the sayings of my mouth.
020	PRO	007	025	Let not thy heart turn aside to her ways, do not go astray on her paths.
020	PRO	007	026	For many deadly wounded hath she caused to fall: yea, very numerous are all those slain by her.
020	PRO	007	027	The ways to the nether world is her house leading down to the chambers of death.
020	PRO	008	001	Behold, wisdom calleth, and understanding sendeth forth her voice,
020	PRO	008	002	On the top of high places, by the wayside, at the house where there are [many] paths doth she place herself.
020	PRO	008	003	Alongside of gates, at the opening of the city, at the entrance of the town[-doors] doth she call loudly,
020	PRO	008	004	Unto you, O men, I call, and my voice [goeth forth] to the sons of men,
020	PRO	008	005	Learn, O ye simple, to understand prudence: and, ye fools, be ye of an understanding heart.
020	PRO	008	006	Hear! for of noble things will I speak; and the opening of my lips shall be of what is equitable.
020	PRO	008	007	For truth uttereth my palate ever, and the abomination of my lips is wickedness.
020	PRO	008	008	In righteousness are all the sayings of my mouth, there is in them nothing crooked or perverse.
020	PRO	008	009	They are all evident to the man of understanding, and correct to those that have obtained knowledge.
020	PRO	008	010	Accept my correction, and not silver; and knowledge rather than choice gold.
020	PRO	008	011	For wisdom is better than pearls; and all the things that men wish for are not equal to her.
020	PRO	008	012	I wisdom dwell with prudence, and the knowledge of discreet thoughts do I discover.
020	PRO	008	013	The fear of the Lord is to hate evil, pride and arrogance, and the evil way: and the mouth of perverseness do I hate.
020	PRO	008	014	Mine are counsel and sound wisdom: I am understanding; mine is might.
020	PRO	008	015	Through me do kings reign, and chieftains give decrees [in] righteousness.
020	PRO	008	016	Through me do princes rule, and the nobles, even all the judges of the earth.
020	PRO	008	017	I indeed love those that love me: and those that seek me earnestly shall find me.
020	PRO	008	018	Riches and honor are with me, yea, enduring wealth and righteousness.
020	PRO	008	019	My fruit is better than gold, and than fine gold; and my products, than choice silver.
020	PRO	008	020	On the road of righteousness do I walk firmly, in the midst the paths of justice:
020	PRO	008	021	That I may cause those that love me to inherit a lasting possession; and their treasures will I fill
020	PRO	008	022	The Lord created me as the beginning of his way, the first of his works from the commencement,
020	PRO	008	023	From eternity was I appointed chief, from the beginning, from the earliest times of the earth.
020	PRO	008	024	When there were yet no depths, was I brought forth; when there were yet no springs laden heavily with water.
020	PRO	008	025	Before the mountains were yet sunk down, before the hills was I brought forth:
020	PRO	008	026	While as yet he had not made the land and open fields, nor the chief of the dust of the world.
020	PRO	008	027	When he prepared the heavens, I was there; when he drew a circle over the face of the deep;
020	PRO	008	028	When he fastened the skies above; when the springs of the deep became strong;
020	PRO	008	029	When he assigned to the sea his decree, that the waters should not transgress his order: when he established firmly the foundations of the earth:
020	PRO	008	030	Then was I near him, as a nursling: and I was day by day [his] delights, playing before him at all times;
020	PRO	008	031	Playing in the world, his earth; and having my delights with the sons of men.
020	PRO	008	032	And now, O children [of men], hearken unto me! for happy those that observe my ways.
020	PRO	008	033	Hear correction, and be wise, and reject it not.
020	PRO	008	034	Happy is the man that hearkeneth unto me, watching day by day at my gates, waiting at the posts of my doors.
020	PRO	008	035	For he who findeth me findeth life, and he obtaineth favor from the Lord.
020	PRO	008	036	But he that sinneth against me doth violence to his own soul: all those that hate me love death.
020	PRO	009	001	Wisdom hath built her house; she hath hewn out her seven pillars;
020	PRO	009	002	She hath killed her cattle; she hath mingled her wine; she hath also set in order her table.
020	PRO	009	003	She hath sent forth her maidens: she inviteth [her guests] upon the top of the highest places of the town.
020	PRO	009	004	Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither: as for him that is void of sense, she saith to him,
020	PRO	009	005	“Come, eat of my bread, and drink of the wine which I have mingled.
020	PRO	009	006	Forsake simplicity, and live; and go onward on the way of understanding.
020	PRO	009	007	He that correcteth a scorner acquireth for himself abuse; and he that reproveth the wicked getteth himself a blemish.
020	PRO	009	008	Do not correct a scorner, lest he hate thee: reprove a wise man, and he will love thee.
020	PRO	009	009	Give to the wise [instruction], and he will become yet wiser: impart knowledge to the righteous, and he will increase his information.
020	PRO	009	010	The commencement of wisdom is the fear of the Lord; and the knowledge of the Most Holy One is understanding.
020	PRO	009	011	For through me shall thy days be multiplied, and the years of thy life shall be increased unto thee.
020	PRO	009	012	If thou art become wise, thou art wise for thyself; but if thou art a scorner, thou alone wilt have to bear it.”
020	PRO	009	013	The woman of folly is noisy: she is simple, and knoweth not what [to do].
020	PRO	009	014	And she sitteth at the door of her house, upon a chair in the high places of the town.
020	PRO	009	015	To call the wayfarers who go straight forward on their paths.
020	PRO	009	016	Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither; and as for him that is void of sense, she saith to him,
020	PRO	009	017	“Stolen waters are sweet, and bread of secrecy is pleasant.”
020	PRO	009	018	But he knoweth not that the departed are there; that in the depths of the nether world are her guests.
020	PRO	010	001	The proverbs of Solomon. A wise son causeth [his] father to rejoice; but a foolish son is the grief of his mother.
020	PRO	010	002	Treasures of wickedness will not profit aught; but righteousness will deliver from death.
020	PRO	010	003	The Lord will not suffer the soul of the righteous to famish; but the sinful desires of the wicked will he cast away.
020	PRO	010	004	He becometh poor that laboreth with an indolent hand, but the hand of the diligent maketh rich.
020	PRO	010	005	He that gathereth in summer is an intelligent son; [but] he that sleepeth in harvest is a son that causeth shame.
020	PRO	010	006	Blessings come upon the head of the righteous; but the mouth of the wicked covereth violence.
020	PRO	010	007	The memory of the just is [destined] to be blessed; but the name of the wicked shall rot.
020	PRO	010	008	The wise in heart will accept commandments; but he that is a fool in his speaking will stumble.
020	PRO	010	009	He that walketh uprightly ever walketh securely; but he that perverteth his ways will be punished.
020	PRO	010	010	He that winketh with the eye causeth vexation; and he that is a fool in his speaking will stumble.
020	PRO	010	011	A source of life is the mouth of the righteous; but the mouth of the wicked covereth violence.
020	PRO	010	012	Hatred stirreth up strifes; but love throweth a cover over all transgressions.
020	PRO	010	013	On the lips of the man of understanding there is found wisdom: but a rod is for the back of him that is void of sense.
020	PRO	010	014	Wise men treasure up knowledge; but the mouth of the foolish is an approaching terror.
020	PRO	010	015	The wealth of the rich man is his strong town: the terror of the poor is their poverty.
020	PRO	010	016	The labor of the righteous [tendeth] to life: the product of the wicked is for sin.
020	PRO	010	017	On the way unto life is he that observeth correction; but he that forsaketh reproof is in error.
020	PRO	010	018	He that hideth hatred hath lips of falsehood; and he that spreadeth abroad an evil report, is a fool.
020	PRO	010	019	In a multitude of words transgression cannot be avoided; but he that refraineth his lips is intelligent.
020	PRO	010	020	[Like] choice silver is the tongue of the righteous: the heart of the wicked is worth but very little.
020	PRO	010	021	The lips of the righteous feed many: but fools die through lack of sense.
020	PRO	010	022	The blessing of the Lord it is which maketh rich, and painful labor addeth nothing thereto.
020	PRO	010	023	It is as sport to a fool to do wicked deeds; but a man of understanding hath wisdom.
020	PRO	010	024	What the wicked dreadeth, that will come upon him: but the longing of the righteous will God grant.
020	PRO	010	025	As the whirlwind passeth by, the wicked is no more; but the righteous is an everlasting foundation.
020	PRO	010	026	As vinegar is to the teeth, and as smoke is to the eyes: so is the sluggard to those that send him.
020	PRO	010	027	The fear of the Lord increaseth [man's] days; but the years of the wicked will be shortened.
020	PRO	010	028	The expectation of the righteous is joy; but the hope of the wicked shall perish.
020	PRO	010	029	The way of the Lord is a stronghold to the upright; but terror is destined to the workers of injustice.
020	PRO	010	030	The righteous shall never be removed; but the wicked shall not inhabit the earth.
020	PRO	010	031	The mouth of the just uttereth wisdom; but the tongue of perverseness shall be cut out.
020	PRO	010	032	The lips of the righteous know [how to obtain] favor; but the mouth of the wicked [speaketh] perverseness.
020	PRO	011	001	Balances of deceit are an abomination of the Lord; but a full weight [obtaineth] his favor.
020	PRO	011	002	When pride cometh, then cometh disgrace; but with the modest there is wisdom.
020	PRO	011	003	The integrity of the upright guideth them; but the cunning of the treacherous destroyeth them.
020	PRO	011	004	Wealth cannot profit on the day of wrath; but righteousness deliver from death.
020	PRO	011	005	The righteousness of the perfect maketh even his way; but by his own wickedness will the wicked fall.
020	PRO	011	006	The righteousness of the upright will deliver them; but through their own sinful desires are the treacherous caught.
020	PRO	011	007	When a wicked man dieth, [his] hope vanisheth; and the expectation of his children is lost.
020	PRO	011	008	The righteous is delivered out of distress, and the wicked cometh in his stead.
020	PRO	011	009	With his mouth doth the hypocrite destroy his neighbor; but through knowledge are the righteous delivered.
020	PRO	011	010	When it goeth well with the righteous, the town rejoiceth loudly: and when the wicked perish, there is joyful shouting.
020	PRO	011	011	Through the blessing of the upright a city is exalted; but through the mouth of the wicked it is pulled down.
020	PRO	011	012	He that despiseth his neighbor is void of sense; but a man of understanding maintaineth silence.
020	PRO	011	013	He that walketh about as talebearer revealeth secrets; but he that is of a faithful spirit concealeth the matter.
020	PRO	011	014	Where there is no wise guidance, a people must fall: but [it will obtain] help through the multitude of counsellors.
020	PRO	011	015	With evil will he be overwhelmed that is surety for a stranger: but he that hateth giving the hand as pledge is safe.
020	PRO	011	016	A woman endowed with grace will surely obtain honor; and the powerful will obtain riches.
020	PRO	011	017	The man of kindness doth good to his own soul; but he that troubleth his own flesh is cruel.
020	PRO	011	018	The wicked practiseth a work of falsehood; but he that soweth righteousness [obtaineth] the reward of truth.
020	PRO	011	019	He who is firm in righteousness attaineth to life: and he that pursueth evil [doth it] to his own death.
020	PRO	011	020	An abomination of the Lord are those of a perverse heart; but his favor is for those who are unblemished in their way.
020	PRO	011	021	The hand [of God] being against [his] hand, the bad man shall not go unpunished; but the seed of the righteous shall escape.
020	PRO	011	022	As a golden ring in a swine's snout, so is a handsome woman that hath thrown off discretion.
020	PRO	011	023	The desire of the righteous is only good: but the hope of the wicked is the wrath [of God].
020	PRO	011	024	There is a man that scattereth gifts, and yet his wealth is increased: and there is one that withholdeth more than is proper, and still cometh only to want.
020	PRO	011	025	A beneficent soul will be abundantly gratified; and he that refresheth [others] will be also refreshed himself.
020	PRO	011	026	Him that withholdeth corn, the people will denounce; but blessing will be heaped upon the head of the one that selleth it.
020	PRO	011	027	He that diligently searcheth after good seeketh favor; but if one inquireth after evil, it will come unto him.
020	PRO	011	028	He that trusteth in his riches will surely fall; but the righteous shall grow like the leaves [of a tree].
020	PRO	011	029	He that troubleth his own house will inherit the wind; and the fool will become the servant to the wise of heart.
020	PRO	011	030	The fruit of the righteous is of the tree of life, and the wise draweth souls to himself.
020	PRO	011	031	Behold, the righteous is recompensed on the earth: how much more the wicked and the sinner.
020	PRO	012	001	Whoso loveth correction loveth knowledge; but he that hateth reproof is brutish.
020	PRO	012	002	The good obtaineth favor of the Lord; but a man of wicked devices will he condemn.
020	PRO	012	003	A man cannot be firmly established by wickedness; but the root of the righteous will not be moved.
020	PRO	012	004	A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband: but as rottenness in his bones is one that bringeth shame [on him].
020	PRO	012	005	The thoughts of the righteous are justice: the best counsels of the wicked are deceit.
020	PRO	012	006	The words of the wicked are of lying in wait for blood; but the mouth of the upright will deliver them.
020	PRO	012	007	The wicked are suddenly overthrown, and are no more; but the house of the righteous will endure.
020	PRO	012	008	In accordance with his intelligence is a man praised; but he that is perverse of heart will come to be despised.
020	PRO	012	009	Better is he that is lightly esteemed who hath a servant, than he that aimeth after honor, and lacketh bread.
020	PRO	012	010	A righteous man careth for the life of his beast; but the mercies of the wicked are cruelty.
020	PRO	012	011	He that tilleth his ground will be satisfied with bread; but he that runneth after idle persons is void of sense.
020	PRO	012	012	The wicked is covetous for the net of evil men; but [God] giveth root to the righteous.
020	PRO	012	013	In the transgression of his lips is the snare of the wicked; but the righteous cometh out of distress.
020	PRO	012	014	From the fruit of his mouth will a man be satisfied with what is good; and the recompense of a man's hands will be brought back unto him.
020	PRO	012	015	The way of a fool is straight in his own eyes; but he that hearkeneth unto counsel is wise.
020	PRO	012	016	The wrath of the fool is known on the very day; but he that concealeth the disgrace is prudent.
020	PRO	012	017	He that uttereth truth announceth righteousness; but a false witness, deceit.
020	PRO	012	018	There is some one that useth words [which are] like the thrusts of a sword; but the tongue of the wise is healing.
020	PRO	012	019	The lip of truth will stand firm for ever; but only for a moment the tongue of falsehood.
020	PRO	012	020	Deceit is in the heart of those that contrive evil; but for the counsellors of peace there is joy.
020	PRO	012	021	No wrong can come unawares to the righteous; but the wicked are full of evil.
020	PRO	012	022	An abomination of the Lord are lips of falsehood; but they that deal in faithfulness [obtain] his favor.
020	PRO	012	023	A prudent man concealeth [his] knowledge; but the heart of fools proclaimeth [their] folly.
020	PRO	012	024	The hand of the diligent will bear rule; but the indolent must become tributary.
020	PRO	012	025	If there be care in the heart of man, let him suppress it; and a good word will change it into joy.
020	PRO	012	026	The righteous is more excellent than his neighbor; but the way of the wicked leadeth them astray.
020	PRO	012	027	The indolent roasteth not that which he hath caught in hunting; but the most precious wealth of man is diligence.
020	PRO	012	028	On the path of righteousness there is life; and on her pathway there is immortality,
020	PRO	013	001	A wise son [becometh so] by the correction of his father; but a scorner hearkeneth not to rebuke.
020	PRO	013	002	From the fruit of a man's mouth doth he eat what is good; but the longing of the treacherous is for violence.
020	PRO	013	003	He that watcheth his mouth guardeth his soul; but he that openeth wide his lips [prepareth] himself destruction.
020	PRO	013	004	The sluggard longeth [in] his soul, and there [cometh] nothing; but the soul of the diligent will be abundantly gratified.
020	PRO	013	005	The righteous hateth the word of falsehood; but the wicked bringeth shame and dishonor.
020	PRO	013	006	Righteousness keepeth [him that is] upright on his way; but wickedness perverteth the [man of] sin.
020	PRO	013	007	There is some one that pretendeth to be rich without having any thing; another that pretendeth to be poor while having abundant wealth.
020	PRO	013	008	As the ransom of a man's life [hath he often to give] his riches; but the poor heareth no threat.
020	PRO	013	009	The light of the righteous burneth joyfully; but the lamp of the wicked will be quenched.
020	PRO	013	010	Only through presumptuous conduct doth man produce contention; but with the well-advised is wisdom.
020	PRO	013	011	Wealth [gotten] by vain deeds will be diminished; but he that gathereth by close labor will increase it.
020	PRO	013	012	Expectation long deferred maketh the heart sick; but a tree of life is a desire which is fulfilled.
020	PRO	013	013	Whoso despiseth the word shall fall in debt to it; but he that feareth the commandment will be rewarded.
020	PRO	013	014	The instruction of the wise is a source of life, [teaching] to avoid the snares of death.
020	PRO	013	015	Good intelligence giveth grace; but the way of the treacherous is hard.
020	PRO	013	016	Every prudent man acteth with knowledge; but a fool spreadeth abroad his folly.
020	PRO	013	017	A wicked messenger falleth into unhappiness; but a faithful ambassador [bringeth] healing.
020	PRO	013	018	Poverty and disgrace will overtake him that rejecteth correction; but he that observeth admonition will be honored.
020	PRO	013	019	A desire accomplished is pleasant to the soul; but it is abomination to fools to depart from evil.
020	PRO	013	020	He that walketh with wise men will become wise; but he that associateth with fools will be destroyed.
020	PRO	013	021	Evil pursueth the sinners; but the righteous will [God] repay with happiness.
020	PRO	013	022	A good man leaveth an inheritance to his children's children; but the wealth of the sinner is treasured up for the righteous.
020	PRO	013	023	Much food bringeth the new-tilled ground of the poor; but there are many others that are taken away through injustice.
020	PRO	013	024	He that withholdeth his rod hateth his son; but he that loveth him chastiseth him betimes.
020	PRO	013	025	The righteous eateth to satisfy his desire [to eat]; but the belly of the wicked always suffereth want.
020	PRO	014	001	The wise among women buildeth her house; but the foolish pulleth it down with her own hands.
020	PRO	014	002	In his uprightness walketh he that feareth the Lord; but perverse in his ways is he that despiseth him.
020	PRO	014	003	In the mouth of the foolish is a stick [for his] pride; but the lips of the wise will preserve them.
020	PRO	014	004	Where no oxen are, is the crib clean; but the abundance of harvests is [only] through the strength of the ox.
020	PRO	014	005	A faithful witness will not lie; but a false witness constantly uttereth lies.
020	PRO	014	006	A scorner seeketh wisdom, and there is none; but knowledge is easy to the man of understanding.
020	PRO	014	007	Go far away from a foolish man, else thou wilt [never] know the lips of knowledge.
020	PRO	014	008	The wisdom of the prudent is to understand his way; but the folly of fools is deceit.
020	PRO	014	009	The fool maketh a mockery of guilt; but among the upright there is good will.
020	PRO	014	010	The heart knoweth its own bitterness; and with its joy can no stranger intermeddle.
020	PRO	014	011	The house of the wicked will be destroyed: but the tent of the upright will flourish.
020	PRO	014	012	There is many a way which seemeth even before a man; but its end are ways unto death.
020	PRO	014	013	Even in laughter the heart feeleth pain; and at its end joy is sorrow.
020	PRO	014	014	The backslider in heart will have enough of his own ways; and from him [departeth] the good men.
020	PRO	014	015	The simple believeth every word; but the prudent man understandeth his steps.
020	PRO	014	016	A wise man is fearful, and departeth from evil; but the fool exciteth himself, and is confident.
020	PRO	014	017	He that is soon angry committeth folly; and a man of wicked devices is hated.
020	PRO	014	018	The simple inherit folly; but the prudent crown themselves with knowledge.
020	PRO	014	019	The bad sink down before the good; and the wicked are at the gates of the righteous.
020	PRO	014	020	Even to his own neighbor is the poor man hateful; but the friends of the rich are many.
020	PRO	014	021	He that despiseth his neighbor is a sinner; but he that is gracious to the poor—happiness attend him!
020	PRO	014	022	Behold, those who contrive evil are in error; but kindness and truth attend on those who contrive what is good.
020	PRO	014	023	In all painful labor there is profit; but mere words of the lips [lead] only to want.
020	PRO	014	024	The crown of the wise is their riches; but the folly of fools is [only] folly.
020	PRO	014	025	A deliverer of souls is the true witness; but a witness of deceit uttereth lies.
020	PRO	014	026	In the fear of the Lord is the strong confidence [of man], and unto his children will it be a place of shelter.
