020	PRO	025	023	The north wind bringeth forth rain: so doth secret talking, angry countenances.
020	PRO	025	024	It is better to dwell in the corner of a roof, than with a quarrelsome woman even in a roomy house.
020	PRO	025	025	As cold water is to a fainting soul, so are good news from a far-off country.
020	PRO	025	026	Like a turbid spring and a corrupt fountain, is a righteous man that giveth way before the wicked.
020	PRO	025	027	To eat too much honey is not good: so is it honor to set a limit to men's honor.
020	PRO	025	028	Like a city that is broken in, and is without walls: so is the man that hath no control over his spirit.
020	PRO	026	001	As snow is in summer, and as rain in harvest: so is honor not seemly to a fool.
020	PRO	026	002	As the bird [cometh] to flit away, as the swallow, to fly off: so will an undeserved curse not come [to fulfillment].
